title: peanut brittle
directions: Heat sugar, Karo and water until sugar melts.
Add dash of salt and nuts.
Cook to hard crack stage.
Take off heat and add soda and stir.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet.
When cool, break in pieces.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar and soda; cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir yeast mix and buttermilk into other ingredients.
Roll and cut as desired.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dough may be covered and refrigerated as long as a week. Can also be made into biscuits and frozen.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to traditional recipe.
Combine all ingredients; pour into casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Mix flour, chopped nuts and oleo well.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1/2 of large Cool Whip in mixer.
Put on crust layer.
Mix pudding and cold milk with mixer; spread on second layer.
Top with rest of Cool Whip and then nuts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Place dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well, beating at low speed.
Pour into greased and floured tin cans.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until baked through.
Cool in tins for 10 minutes.

title: 90 day pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; pack in big mouth, glass gallon jar.
Cover cucumbers with vinegar and add alum, allspice, cloves and salt. Put on jar lid and leave it for 90 days.
At the end of 90 days, drain off vinegar and spices, then slice the cucumbers and return to gallon jar.
Cover with sugar; set aside and occasionally tilt jar to help melt the sugar.
The sugar will draw the vinegar out of the pickles to make a liquid to cover the pickles.
You may put in smaller jars and seal.
These are good pickles and so easy to make.

title: easy milk way pie
directions: Add lemon juice to pie filling and place into shell.
Thinly slice candy bars over top.
Sprinkle nuts on top and bake in 450° oven for ten minutes.
Reduce temperature to 375° and continue baking ten to fifteen minutes more.
Cool.
Serve with lightly sweetened, vanilla flavored whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add pineapple, eggs and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or longer.
Do not mix with a beater. Mix with a spoon.

title: pizzelle (cookies)
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually.
Beat until smooth.
Add cooled melted margarine and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder and eggs.
Dough will be sticky enough to be dropped by spoon. Place a heaping teaspoon of batter in the center of each grid pattern on the bottom grid to make full size pizzelles.
Close grids; squeeze handles together to spread batter and clip handles together during baking.
Bake until golden brown.
Baking time is approximately 1/2 minute.
Remove pizzelles from grid with a spatula.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix in other ingredients.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Place vanilla wafers in miniature cupcake papers and tins.
Put tablespoon of filling on each wafer.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
When cool, put jelly or cherry pie filling on top. Keep cool until served.
Makes 5 or 6 dozen.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Crush cornflakes to make 1 cup crumbs.
Set aside.
In small saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Remove from heat; stir in salt and pepper.
Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Brush with butter mixture.
Place crushed cornflakes or bread crumbs on a sheet of wax paper; roll chicken in crumbs to coat.
Arrange chicken, skin side up and so pieces don't touch, in shallow baking pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Do not turn.

title: fruit salad
directions: Whip the cream and add 2 tablespoons of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla; add all ingredients.
Chill!

title: paul newman cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, bake cake according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, combine pineapple and 3/4 cup sugar.
Cook over medium heat until thick and syrupy (20 minutes).
When cake is done, remove from oven and pierce with fork at 1-inch intervals.
Pour on pineapple mixture and spread over cake; cool completely.
Mix the pudding mix and milk; spread over cooled cake.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding and sprinkle coconut on top.
May garnish top with Thank You Brand cherry pie filling, leaving off coconut.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: In large skillet, saute zucchini and onion in butter until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in seasonings.

title: oatmeal crispies cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well. Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add oats and roll in wax paper.
Chill thoroughly.
Slice thin and bake in moderate oven, about 350°.

title: chicken and pasta(with garlic and herb sauce)
directions: Saute chicken in olive oil. Drain on paper towels then dice in large pieces. Cook pasta and sauce mix according to package directions. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Salt and pepper to taste. Top with parmesan and serve.

title: sour cream
directions: Add a little vinegar to milk.

title: fresh fried mushrooms
directions: Soak mushrooms overnight in salt water.
Keep in refrigerator. Next day, rinse with plain water.
Drain.
Cover with flour; add to oil and butter in skillet.
Cook slowly.
Add salts.
Turn gently.
Fry for about 5 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: asparagus, green pea casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Alternate layers of asparagus, green peas and sour cream.
Dice capers and sprinkle over mixture.
Add salt and black pepper to mixture.
Cover mixture with bread crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spinach noodles
directions: Cook noodles in salted water until tender; drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Put in slow cooker.
Cover; cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: luau refresher
directions: In a large non-metal punch bowl or pitcher, combine pineapple juice, concentrates and water. Just before serving, add ginger ale, stirring gently. Serve with ice ring or ice cubes and fresh fruit slices. Makes 19 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: marinated italian salad
directions: Mix all together. Chill.

title: my homemade pea beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in large dish with water just over the top of beans.
Drain beans, saving water beans were in.
Divide beans into 2 crock-pots with other ingredients in order as they are in.
Add enough water to cover beans.
Cook on high for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring gently from time to time. Turn down on low and cook for 4 to 6 hours.

title: grilled clams parmesan
directions: Scrub clams in cold water. Drain in cold water.
Mix butter, lemon juice and garlic powder.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter gradually adding sugar. Beat until light.
Add egg, vanilla and milk.
Beat thoroughly. Mix flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Roll dough to 1/4 inch thickness and cut into shapes.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat shortening with an electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and molasses.
Beat well.
Set aside.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Cut grapes in half.
Cut English walnuts into medium pieces. Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pour whipping cream over mixture.

title: best fruit cake ever
directions: Pour dry ingredients over fruit; mix very well. Beat 3 eggs with vanilla, then pour over coated fruit and mix well. Put in greased and floured spring-form tube pan. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°, until toothpick comes out clean. Do not overbake.

title: pizza turnovers
directions: Saute mushrooms, green pepper and onion in margarine.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in cheese.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix together and place in 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mabel's english pea casserole
directions: Drain peas and pimento.
Cook white sauce according to directions.
Combine all ingredients with white sauce.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak in small amount of cooking oil.
Add onions, soup, mushrooms and seasonings.
Simmer until meat is tender (covered). Thicken gravy to desired consistency by adding cornstarch in small amount of water.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream while still hot.
(Do not boil, sour cream will curdle.)
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: white chocolate popcorn
directions: Mix all these together in large bowl or roaster pan. Melt one 24 ounce package of almond bark and combine 1/2 cup peanut butter. Pour over other mixture and toss to coat all well. Pour onto cookie sheets or wax paper. When set, break into chunks and serve. Stores well in Tupperware.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and pack into hot sterilized jars.
Put 1 pepper pod and 1 garlic clove in each jar.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil; water, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Pour over okra and seal.
Set jars in simmering water and process for 10 minutes and let set for 8 weeks.

title: brown county oatmeal cookies
directions: Optional:
Substitute 1 1/2 cups sugar for honey and use 1/2 cup buttermilk.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pack meat mixture into a greased 8x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Bake 45 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: coffee-orange fudge cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, oil, water, eggs, pudding, coffee, orange peel and cinnamon.
Beat on low until blended, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 4 minutes.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Pour into large greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool 10 minutes on wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serves 24.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix all at
once
and bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round pans.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown lightly in saucepan the olive oil, onion and garlic. Add and simmer for 15 minutes the Italian tomatoes, parsley, basil leaves, salt and pepper and tomato paste.

title: shish kabob marinade
directions: Mix together.
Marinate steak and mushrooms about 3 to 4 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar in a plastic bag; place biscuit pieces in and shake until coated.
Place coated pieces in an ungreased Bundt pan.
Melt butter with 1 cup sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Heat and pour hot mixture over biscuit pieces. Toss lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine cornstarch, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Add margarine.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium-high heat and boil 1 minute. Remove from
heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the cheese until melted.
Add macaroni.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole. Combine remaining 1/2 cup of cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: deviled frankfurters
directions: Split franks lengthwise almost, but not quite through.
Spread cut surfaces with mustard.

Place slice of cheese in each split. Wrap slice of bacon around each frank and fasten with toothpicks. Can be fried slow until bacon is crispy, can be broiled under medium heat or can be put on barbecue grill.

title: alfredo fettucine
directions: Prepare noodles to package directions, drain. Add butter and shredded cheese. Stir until melted. Add cream, stir until well blended.

title: little applesauce muffins
directions: In large bowl, cream softened butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs one at a time until light and fluffy. Beat in applesauce. Stir together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to butter mixture. Stir just enough to moisten. Spoon into 36 greased tea-sized muffin cups. Bake in preheated 425° oven about 15 minutes. While warm, dip tops into melted butter and cinnamon sugar. Serve warm.

title: irish sherry trifle
directions: Slice jelly roll and arrange in glass bowl.
Pour sherry over cake.
Slice bananas and arrange over cake.
Make Jell-O according to directions and pour over items in bowl.
Let set.
Make vanilla pudding (I use Birds Custard).
Cool and pour over bananas, etc.
Chill.
Cover with whipped cream before serving.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate chips with sweetened condensed milk and margarine.
In large bowl, combine peanuts and marshmallows.
Pour chocolate mixture into nut mixture and mix well.
Spread into wax-paper lined 13 x 9-inch dish.
Chill 2 hours or more.
Cut into squares.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions. Bake in greased and floured 9x13 inch pan.
Cool. Poke holes in top of cake with skewer or toothpick.
Cook pineapple and sugar 5 minutes.
Cool and then pour mixture over cake.
Mix pudding mix and milk.
Allow to thicken.
Top with coconut, then pudding, cool whip and finally with pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: gazpacho
directions: Put 2 cups juice in blender.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend well; add remaining juice.
Chill well.
Serves 8.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use. Yields 1 3/4 cups (approximately the same as one 14-ounce can and may be made at a fraction of the cost and the calories).
Also, may be stored in the refrigerator for several weeks.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix all for 2 minutes.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes and then poke with fork.
Spoon on glaze.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute rice and onion in butter and skillet until lightly browned.
Add water and bouillon cube.
Bring to a boil, stirring until cube is dissolved.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour, margarine and confectioners sugar together.
Press into pizza pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix glaze and strawberries; put on top of Cool Whip.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Add sour cream, eggs and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients together and add to other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar icing.
Makes 8 dozen bite size cookies.

title: zucchini, green chili casserole
directions: Slice zucchini thin and boil in lightly salted water for 3 minutes.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer rice, chiles, half of the cheese, zucchini and tomatoes.
Mix sour cream with seasoned salt, green pepper and onion.
Pour over casserole and then add rest of cheese.
Sprinkle top with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mango salad
directions: Blend mangos with syrup and cream cheese (use blender). Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine mango mixture with Jell-O.
Pour
into mayonnaise lined pan.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: banana pudding
directions: Substitute 1 cup coconut instead of bananas and cookies for Coconut Cream Pie Filling.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine and place in an 8 x 8-inch casserole pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: crabmeat dip appetizer
directions: Spread cheese on tray.
Mix sauce and crabmeat, stir until blended.
Spread evenly over cream cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: missy's cream cheese cookies
directions: Stir together the flour and salt.

Beat the butter. Add cream cheese, orange rind and sugar. Beat thoroughly until fluffy, texture of mayonnaise. Beat in egg yolk. Stir in flour mixture, all at once, until blended, then chocolate and walnuts. Drop by level tablespoonfuls 1-inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly with a small spatula. Bake in a moderate 350° oven about 15 minutes or until cookie edges are brown. Tops will be cream color.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cook sugar until spins a good thread; add to well beaten eggs. Add melted butter, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix together and let set overnight.

title: taco party wings
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a plastic bag.
Shake wings, a few at a time, until well coated.
Place in a single layer on a greased shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Turn wings and bake 10 minutes or until tender.

title: country chicken
directions: Line bottom of cookie sheet with beef.
Place chicken on top of beef and cover with the soup mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with flavored rice, such as curry or saffron vs. vegetable and salad.

title: pork chops and scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Slice thinly into a deep casserole dish. Sprinkle with flour; salt and pepper to taste.
Dot with margarine.
Pour milk over potatoes.
Lay chops on top of potatoes to form a layer and sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until chops are done.

title: honey crunch
directions: Combine the corn bran cereal, oats, nuts, cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Combine margarine, honey and brown sugar in pan; cook over low heat until well blended.
Pour over cereal mixture. Spread on 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 325° until golden brown, stirring occasionally.
Spread onto waxed paper.
Stir in the raisins.
Cool.
Store in tight container in cool, dry place.
Freezes well.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil ingredients 3 minutes.
Fill wide mouth jar with hard-boiled peeled eggs.
Pour hot juice over eggs.
Put lids on jars and cool to room temperature, then refrigerate.
Will keep several weeks.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients over a low fire until blended.
In a 3 or 4-quart baking dish, put down a layer of chips and top with chicken.
Sprinkle with corn and cover with sauce.
Repeat layering, using remaining ingredients, with the sauce as the final layer.
Cook in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Let sit for 15 or 20 minutes before serving.

title: cherry chiffon pie
directions: Drain cherries.
Heat sugar in 1/2 cup juice and cool.
Mix gelatin in water.
Add gelatin, flavoring and cherries.
Add egg whites that have been beaten stiff with cream of tartar.
Add whipped cream and pour into 9-inch baked pie crust.

title: beer steak
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add steak and brown on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from skillet and place in a shallow baking pan.
Mix together soup mix, beer, vinegar, celery, carrots, sugar, tomato sauce, thyme and parsley flakes.
Pour over steak.
Bake covered in 300° oven for 2 hours and 30 minutes or until steak is tender.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onions.
Drain off grease.
Add mushroom soup and water.
Simmer a little, then add cooked rice.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Mix sausage, crackers, eggs and sage and shape into 1-inch balls.
Saute in frypan and drain.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally and serve hot on picks.
Can be frozen in sauce and defrosted in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Saut onion and peppers in small amount of oil until tender. Add ground beef and cook until browned; drain well.
Add enchilada seasoning, tomato paste and 1 3/4 cups water.
Simmer, uncovered, on low until liquid is absorbed.
On each tortilla, spread meat mixture, 1 tablespoon sour cream and Monterey Jack cheese.
Roll up and place in casserole dish.
Pour enchilada sauce over top and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 300° until cheese melts, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: just brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix all together and you have a delicious and festive holiday salad.

title: cowboy pot roast
directions: Brown garlic and onion in 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a Dutch oven or large casserole, remove and reserve.
Add remaining olive oil and meat, browning on all sides.
Add water, parsley, bay leaf, pepper, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce, if using. Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Add reserved garlic and onion, potatoes, carrots, celery and turnip; cook an additional hour. (This also can be done in a 325° oven in a covered roasting pan.)

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Combine cocoa, cinnamon, flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Stir in applesauce.
Pour in a well-greased and floured Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ribbon meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together bread and milk; mix in remaining ingredients.
Put one half of meat mixture in a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover with cheese filling. Top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Take ice cream out of the freezer to soften.
Mix softened ice cream with cookies and Cool Whip.
Spoon mixture into a large tube pan.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, put tube pan in 2 inches warm water for a few seconds.
Invert tube pan onto a plate and serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend sugar, spices and salt together.
Beat eggs with evaporated milk and combine with sugar, spices and pumpkin until smooth.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shells.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 15 minutes; reduce heat to moderate (350°).
Continue baking 35 minutes or until knife inserted in pie comes out clean. Cool before serving.

title: vichyssoise(cold potato soup)
directions: Melt butter in heavy soup kettle.
Saute onions until golden and soft.
Add potatoes, chicken broth, salt and pepper; simmer on low heat until potatoes are very soft, even mushy.
Blend or puree mixture in a food processor or press through a sieve with a wooden spoon.
Return to kettle.

title: pear salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot pear juice.
Add cream cheese while still hot.
Beat with eggbeater to mix cheese evenly in jello.
When cool and set like syrup, add pears that have been mashed.
Add whipped cream last.
May also add mandarin oranges, if desired.

title: devil's food cake mix brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir and press batter into greased 9 x 14-inch pan.
Batter will be very thick.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes for a chewy type brownie, slightly longer for cake type.
These are extra good and easy.

title: cucumber-yogurt salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and refrigerate.
Good with chicken or fish.
All measurements are approximate, more or less to taste.
This Persian dish can also be prepared without cucumber.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Put hamburger into baking dish.
Add diced onions on top of meat.
Add diced celery.
Add tomato soup.
Add generous layer of potatoes.
Add mushroom soup.
Add milk.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: champion date salad(in honor of "hal dale")
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat in maple syrup until creamy.
Add dates, marshmallows, pecans and pineapple.
Stir until all is blended well.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip.
Let cool in refrigerator for 30 minutes so flavors will blend before serving.
Great the next day, also; ready to serve anytime after, at least 30 minutes.

title: blackberry cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, flour and salt.
Place blackberries in pastry shell.
Spread sour cream mixture on top.
Combine bread crumbs, the 2 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Sprinkle atop. Bake in a 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: peggy's famous mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Beat in cream cheese, sour cream, garlic powder and onion salt.
Put in buttered casserole dish. Dot with butter and sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cover for the first 1/2 hour, then uncover and continue baking.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Whip all ingredients together.
Season with celery salt to taste.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix a small amount of apple cider with red hots. Melt well and add remaining apple cider. Place in coffee maker and keep warm. Serve warm.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans with soup and milk.
Top with onion rings. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Melt first 5 ingredients in double boiler. Cut a loaf of sourdough or firm textured bread into cubes (remove crust). When cheese is melted and still over heat, break 1 egg at a time and beat until smooth after each egg. Dip bread cubes into cheese mixture and place on cookie sheet. Freeze and then bag.

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly.
Pat dry.
Mix seasonings in plastic bag; shake.
Place chicken in flour mixture, then in egg-milk mixture and back in flour mixture again.
Let set out 1 hour to dry.
Using Crisco oil, fry at 375°.
Brown on all sides.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Using brown paper bag with paper towels, this keeps chicken warm also.

title: honey bunch cookies
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar.
Bring to boil.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Line foil with a package of graham crackers, whole or divided into fourths.
Sprinkle crackers with pecans. Pour boiled mixture over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift flour with baking powder and add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and fold in nuts.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Grease a large oblong casserole. Mix all ingredients together until well blended. Spread evenly in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Cool slightly, then cut into serving size squares.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix all but flour with mixer.
Add flour and beat with spoon. Add flour to knead.
Knead and put in buttered bowl and let rise in buttered bowl.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients down to mayonnaise.
Set aside.
Add eggs to mayonnaise; toss gently.
Add to chicken.
Stir well.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Spread on seasoned crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Line bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan with nuts and coconut.
Mix cake mix as per box directions.
Pour over coconut and nuts.
Mix confectioners sugar and cream cheese with margarine.
Spoon into cake mix.
Do not stir.
Bake at 300° to 350° for about 55 minutes.

title: e-z peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and peaches.
Melt butter in pan or dish.
Pour batter in and add peach halves, juice and all. Bake for 40 minutes.

title: pickled corn
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, honey, vinegar, water, salt, celery seed, mustard seed and onion.
Bring to boiling and boil 2 minutes.
Add corn pieces.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until corn is tender.
Remove from heat.
Cool to room temperature.
Refrigerate until well chilled.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Rinse wild rice and cover with boiling water and let stand, covered, for at least 2 hours.
Make sure water covers rice by 1 to 2 inches.
Brown meat, onion and green pepper in butter.
Do not season!!
Add soup, mushrooms, soy sauce and hot water.
Use water rice soaked in and put soy sauce into it.
Rice should have been drained.
Add rice to other ingredients.
Bake in large casserole for 1 1/2 hours in 300° oven, covered.
Uncover and bake for 1/2 hour more.
May sprinkle with slivered almond, if desired, just before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: birthday cake for chocoholics
directions: Mix together well before adding chips. Place in greased pan in preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° for 15 to 20 minutes. Let cool. Place candles.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease an oblong pan with butter or Crisco.
Sprinkle pan with nuts and coconut.
Mix together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Set aside.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour cake mix over nuts and coconut.
Spoon globs of cream cheese mixture in cake mix.
Swirl through cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: turkey and apple sandwiches
directions: Spread 1 side of each slice of bread with about 1 tablespoon yogurt.
Top the slices with 1/4 of the turkey; add slices of lettuce.
Place remaining slices of bread on top, yogurt side down. Makes 4 sandwiches.
Low-fat.

title: lentil soup(diabetic approved)
directions: Place all ingredients, except tomato, in a large kettle and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1-1 1/2 hours.
Add tomato and continue simmering, cover for 5 minutes longer.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: knots(cookies)
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine. Add eggs. Add flavoring.
Use mixer. Add dry ingredients.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Refrigerate until chilled, 2 hours. Roll into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes until lightly brown on bottom.

title: corn and potato chowder
directions: Cook onion in margarine in a Dutch oven over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add 2 cups water and next 3 ingredients.
Bring to boil, cover and reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Remove, stir in corn, milk and ham. Combine flour and 1/2 cup water.
Stir until smooth.
Add potato mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: mom's homemade ice cream
directions: Mix flour (or instant pudding), sugar and salt.
Add some of the milk, enough to make a thin paste.
Add vanilla and fruit or candy.
Add up to 1 quart of the milk and mix.
Pour into an ice cream freezer and then add the rest of the milk to the fill line in your freezer.
You don't have to mix, the churning of the freezer will mix it up.
When it begins to be thick, take it out of the freezer and pour it into a 1 gallon ice cream plastic bucket.
Place in the freezer.
You can do this ahead, but not overnight or it will be too hard.

title: farfalle with cilantro salsa
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl. Add pasta and toss gently. Serve at room temperature.

title: german potato salad
directions: Steam potatoes and slice thin while hot.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Cook onion in bacon fat.
Stir in vinegar.
Mix flour, sugar and salt and add to vinegar mixture.
Cook until dressing thickens a little.

title: rice balls
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth until all liquid evaporates (in a covered pot 20 to 25 minutes).
Add butter.
Cool thoroughly. Beat 6 egg yolks.
Add this and grated cheese to rice.
Mix thoroughly.
Form rice into ball.
Insert a Mozzarella cube.
Make sure the rice covers the cube.
Beat 6 egg whites plus 1 egg.
Dip rice balls into egg and roll in bread crumbs to cover completely. Deep fry 4 to 5 at once.
Fry until golden brown, about 10 to 13 minutes.
Keep hot in 250° oven until all balls are fried.
Serve hot.

title: sub kum chop suey
directions: *I use beef stew meat cut in small pieces.

title: cocoa cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat for 3 minutes. Combine flour, cocoa, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with 1 1/3 cups of water.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken(it's quick, easy, and tastes great!)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pour over skinless chicken pieces in a shallow pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oats, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add rest.
Roll into golf ball size balls and place 2 inches apart to bake.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: easy quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into deep dish pie shell. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and butter (oleo).
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Start in cold oven.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in a tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from pan and glaze while warm.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Boil together 10 to 11 minutes. Add margarine, chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts. Beat well until all ingredients are blended together.
Pour into a large buttered pan.
Place into refrigerator.
Makes 6 pounds. Will keep for weeks wrapped well in foil.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir boiling water into jello in a large bowl at least 2 minutes until completely dissolved. Add enough ice to cold water to make 1 cup. Add to jello and stir until ice is melted. Add cool whip and stir until well blended. Refrigerate for 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is very thick. Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mash cookie dough into pizza pan and cook until done and completely cool.
Mix together sugar, vanilla and cream cheese, then spread on top of cookie.
Add rest of ingredients in order.

title: topping for 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Split cake and spread crushed pineapple while cake is hot. Put top on cake. Pour pineapple juice over cake. Mix the Dream Whip. Add cream cheese. Ice cake. Put cherry pie filling on top.

title: italian noodle salad
directions: Mix noodles, vegetables and cheese.
Mix dressings together and pour over noodle mixture.
Mix well.

title: apple johnny
directions: Put sliced apples in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until batter is done.

title: applesauce cake roll
directions: Beat eggs until thick; gradually add sugar and beat well.
Add applesauce.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves; fold in lightly.
Spread on greased and paper-lined jellyroll pan, 15 x 10 x 1-inch.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Loosen and release on cloth sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Roll up; cool and unroll.
Mix applesauce and Cool Whip; spread on cake.
Roll up; slice and top with dabs of whipped cream and chopped nuts.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy and gradually add sugar until meringue stands in peaks.
Fold in other ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch buttered and floured pie pan or spray with Pam.
Cook 45 minutes in a 300° oven.
Cool and serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: short ribs luau
directions: Saute onion in butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Add all other ingredients except ribs.
Simmer covered about 45 minutes.
If sauce is too thick, add 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add short ribs and cook covered about 2 1/2 hours.
Brown under broiler.

title: mary's pot roast
directions: Heat butter in heavy pan with cover.
Pepper meat (do not salt); brown meat on all sides (tomato soup gives you all the salt).
Add onions and celery; saute until onion is limp.
Dilute tomato soup with wine; pour over meat and onion mixture.
Bake in 350° oven (with cover).
Baste frequently.
Last 1/2 hour of baking, remove cover from pan.
Add mushrooms and bake.
Remove meat; cool and slice.

title: apple 'n honey scones
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until light and thick.
Fold grated zucchini into oil mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into zucchini mixture until just blended.
Fold in the walnuts. Pour batter into the buttered loaf pans.
Bake on the middle rack of the oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool slightly; remove from pan and cool completely on a rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Put pie crust in pie plate and flute. Cook ground beef and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in salt, pepper, Bisquick and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into pie shell. Mix eggs and cottage cheese and pour over beef mixture.
Arrange tomato slices on top and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake until set, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: yeast muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat real good.	May use all at once or store
in
refrigerator.
Fill
muffin pans 3/4 full and bake until done.

title: maple baked beans
directions: Place beans in casserole with maple syrup, onion, mustard, pepper and enough water to cover.
Cover with bacon strips.
Bake at about 300° for approximately 3 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place items in microwave-safe bowl in the order given. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir immediately.
Pour into a 7 x 11-inch glass pan.
Cool.
(If you line the pan with Saran Wrap, you can lift it all out of the pan and it makes for easy cleanup.)

title: lost bread?
directions: Beat egg; add salt, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour into shallow dish; dip bread into mixture and let it absorb as much as possible on both sides.
Place slices in well-greased pan and put it in hot oven (400°) until dry and brown.
Nice served with butter and honey.

title: favorite turkey stuffing(for 20 pound bird)
directions: Chop onions and celery and put these with margarine and sausage. Fry together until done. Then add cornbread that has been softened with chicken broth, wild rice, rice and seasoning. Stuff the bird.

title: party pizzas
directions: Mix mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese well.
Spread on each slice of bread; top with 1 or 2 pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Toss lightly and chill.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese and butter together, sift sugar and cocoa.
Mix all together and add vanilla.
May add nuts (optional).
Makes five pounds of candy.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat together and then set aside.
Cut up toppings.

title: eggplant pizza
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Dip eggplant slices in eggs and fry in vegetable oil on high heat until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Arrange eggplant on baking sheet.

title: potato and ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain grease.
Peel potatoes and slice in bottom of pan.
Pour ground beef over potatoes and mix soup with a little water, then pour on top and bake at 375° until potatoes are tender.
Serve with salad and rolls.

title: best banana bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Add flour, soda and salt; mix well. Then add bananas, sour cream and nuts and blend well. Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: turkey rolls
directions: Spoon stuffing on turkey slices and roll together.
Place in an ungreased casserole, folded side down.
Mix soup and 1/2 can of water.
Pour over rolls and bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: marshmallow nut goodies
directions: Melt over low heat the chocolate and butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add marshmallows and nuts; mix well.
Pour into large pan or cookie sheet.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: spanish corn
directions: Chop onion and pepper into small pieces and saute in margarine until tender and slightly brown.
Drain most of the liquid from the corn and pour into small saucepan.
Heat until hot.
Add sugar and sauteed items.
(Red hot sauce and/or Tabasco sauce may be added to taste.)
Cook for 1 minute.
Remove and serve immediately.
Don't prepare too far in advance as corn will discolor.

title: noodle pudding(sweet)
directions: Cook noodles as directed on box (in large pot of salted, boiling water until soft).
Drain noodles thoroughly.
Add to drained noodles the butter, eggs, cream cheese, sugar, apricot nectar and the milk.
Mix together well.
The mixture will be quite loose.
Grease either a square or oblong pan (about 8 x 10-inch).
Grease with butter well; put mixture in.

title: easy make cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Blend in eggs, then stir in chocolate chips.
Pour batter into a ready-made pie crust (graham cracker).
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup mini semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool approximately 3 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar together until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over broccoli and onion mixture.
Toss and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, put bacon and cheese over top and toss.

title: deep dish pork pie
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Add squash, beans and onion.
Saute 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except pastry.
Transfer to 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: blueberry cheesecake(serves 9 to 12)
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and the butter; press firmly and evenly in bottom of ungreased baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored; beat in 1/2 cup sugar, the cream cheese and vanilla until smooth.
Pour over crumb mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top; cool.
In saucepan, mix 1/2 cup sugar and the cornstarch. Stir in reserved blueberry liquid and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in blueberries.
Cool.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream.

title: tortilla with cream cheese filling
directions: Mix and spread over 8 to 10-inch flour tortilla.
Roll up and refrigerate for 12 hours.
Slice thin.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: rum balls
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add vanilla wafers.
Process until crumbs are fine.
Transfer to a large bowl. Place pecans in processor bowl; process until finely chopped. Stir into vanilla wafer crumbs.
Stir in honey, bourbon and rum. Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar or additional vanilla wafer crumbs.
Place in an airtight container and store in the refrigerator up to 4 weeks.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Bake cookies as directed on package.
Let cool.
Combine ice cream and topping.
Line cake pan with cookies.
Spread ice cream mixture over cookies.
Sprinkle with extra cookie crumbs.
Freeze; slice.

title: mud pie(make day before using.)
directions: Crush wafers and add butter.
Mix well.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with soft coffee ice cream.
Put into freezer until ice cream is firm.

title: pattie's muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and then add remaining ingredients.
Keeps 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: deviled clams
directions: Grind clams, bring clam broth to boil; skim.
Add ground clams, milk and butter.
When this mixture boils, add crackers, eggs and seasonings.
Wash shells, fill each with clam mixture. Dot with buttered bread crumbs and brown in oven.
This amount will fill about 40 clam shells.

title: granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix liquid ingredients together, then add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake on cookie sheet at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil this mixture 5 minutes.
Add soda and pour over popped corn and stir.
Put in oven and bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir about every 15 minutes.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Heat water on high in large, deep frying pan on top of stove. Once it boils, add soup mix; stir and add meat.
Brown meat; do not drain.
Add cleaned, cut potatoes, frozen vegetables and basil.
Cover.
Continue to cook on high, stirring and adding water as needed, until all items are fully cooked, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: garden rice
directions: Saute carrots, celery, onion and mushrooms in butter.
Add rice and continue sauteing until rice is brown.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Cover and take off heat.
Rice is ready in 10 minutes.

title: chilled crispy-crust chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces on sheet of waxed paper.
Season generously with salt and pepper on both sides and sprinkle lightly with poultry seasoning.
With pastry brush or spatula, coat on all sides with mayonnaise or salad dressing.
In a paper bag, place corn flake crumbs, salt, pepper, paprika or cayenne pepper; shake to mix.
(Bread crumbs or flour may be substituted for corn flakes).
Drop chicken into bag, one piece at a time, close bag, shake to coat all sides.
Arrange in shallow Pyrex dish or baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Serve chilled with lettuce, tomatoes, cucumbers and additional dressing.
Serves 4.

title: party ham biscuits
directions: Slice entire package of rolls at one time with electric knife. Combine butter and spices in saucepan and heat until butter is melted.
Spread this mixture on bottom layer of rolls.
Place ham on top of this and then sprinkle with cheese.
Put the top of rolls on.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into individual rolls.
Serve hot.

title: hot potato salad
directions: (Our version of hot German potato salad is chock-full of crunchy vegetables.)

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; let stand 1 hour.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil.
Combine with other mixture and boil 5 minutes; put in jars.

title: graham goodies
directions: Boil the margarine and brown sugar together a few minutes.
Add the nuts.
Pour over the whole graham crackers arranged on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry brownie torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease two (9-inch) round layer cake pans. Line with waxed paper, extending up sides of pans. Grease waxed paper.

title: barbecue sausage
directions: Saute sausage; pierce to drain fat.
Remove sausage.
Drain and slice into 1/4-inch thick diagonal slices.
Drain sausage fat from pan except for 1 to 2 tablespoons.
In a pan, saute onion, bell pepper and garlic until soft.
Return sausage to pan.
Add sauces, ketchup, liquid smoke and hot sauce.
Cook, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes over low heat.
Serve in fondue or crock-pot.

title: pear preserves
directions: Wash, peel and core pears.
Slice into long fingers and place in a large container.
Cover with sugar and set aside overnight.

title: microwaved snackin' nuts
directions: In a 1-quart glass measuring cup, melt butter on High 30 seconds.
Add nuts.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring every minute.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and brown sugar; add nuts, coating evenly.
Cool, spreading evenly on breadboard. Serve warm or cold.
Store in freezer for later use, if desired. Makes 2 cups.

title: apple turnovers
directions: *Note:
One 20 to 22 ounce can prepared cherry pie filling may be used in place of apple.

title: mrs. pope's bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar. Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix in all other ingredients and enough white flour to make a good texture.
Put into a greased bowl; let rise until double in bulk (2 hours).
Punch down and let rise again (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Knead well and form into loaves.
Makes 4 large or 6 medium loaves.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Cut steak across the grain into 1/4-inch strips, about 2 inches long.
In large skillet or wok, brown meat in oil.
Push meat to one section of skillet.
Stir in beef broth, sugar and soy sauce.
Place mushrooms, green onions, onions, celery and bamboo shoots in separate section of skillet.
(Do not mix.)
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Add spinach; simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.
If desired, pass additional soy sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spanish rice and chicken
directions: Combine garlic salt, celery salt and paprika; sprinkle over chicken.
Arrange chicken pieces, skin side up, in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Remove chicken from dish.
Combine rice, onions, green pepper and parsley in baking dish; stir well.
Combine chicken broth, tomatoes, chili powder and salt in small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over rice mixture, stirring well.
Arrange chicken pieces over rice.
Cover and bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until chicken and rice are tender.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix until crumbly.
Take half and pack in the bottom of an 8x12-inch pan.
Spread 1 can cherry pie filling over this.
Put the rest of the mix on top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Measure and mix together dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, zucchini and oil in another bowl. Stir all together.
Spoon into muffin pans.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 18 muffins.

title: apple delight
directions: Generously butter an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Peel apples; remove seeds and cut into 8 wedges.
Place wedges in rows as close together as possible in a single layer in pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Combine flour and brown sugar; cut in butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Sprinkle over and between apples and pat smooth.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes. Serve hot or cold, plain or with ice cream.
Freezes well.
Serves 12.

title: christmas fruitcake
directions: Make batter mixing all ingredients but fruit and nuts. Stir in fruit and nuts last. Pour into lightly greased pans and bake at 300° for following time: two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans, bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes; eight 4 x 2-inch pans, bake for 55 minutes and for 48 tart size pans, bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix egg, milk and melted margarine.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to first mixture and beat.

title: portuguese sausage soup
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Add water to beans to cover.
Cook beans with ham hock until soft.
Add chopped vegetables and sausage, cut in bite sizes.
Boil 1/2 hour.
Season to taste.

title: simple and good cheese ball
directions: Blend all together and chill. Shape into ball or log and sprinkle with chopped pecans. Serve with crackers.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugars.
Beat in vanilla, water and egg.
Add sifted flour to sugar and egg mixture and mix well.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese while cold.
Let cheese and sausage reach room temperature and mix together well.
Add Bisquick and mix well. Roll into small or medium balls (firm).
Cook at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all together.
Doesn't take long to set.
This is a large bowl.
I have used half of all ingredients to make a good sized bowl.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Mix.
Beat until thick; pour over crust.
Top with Cool Whip and then chocolate syrup.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease 8-inch square glass pan. Blend all ingredients except apples until crumbly.
Layer apples, then topping.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: For cake:
Combine flour, sugar and soda in a mixing bowl; set aside.
Combine margarine, water and 1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa. Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add the chocolate mixture to dry ingredients and beat on medium speed until combined.
Add eggs, 1/2 cup buttermilk and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Beat one minute; batter will be thin.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook beef roast (boiled or roasted).
When roast is done, cut into slices.
Prepare soup as directed on can.
Add roast and green pepper to soup.
Simmer for 1 hour or until roast is tender. Serve on sliced kaiser rolls.

title: bread pudding
directions: Use enough bread pieces to fill 8 x 8-inch dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar, raisins and cinnamon over crumbs.
Melt butter in milk and blend in eggs.
Pour mixture over bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with Sauce.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and water in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil until sugar dissolves.
Stick 2 cloves in each peach and add peaches to syrup.
Cook until soft and put in jars.
Cover with syrup and seal.

title: edible peanut butter play dough
directions: Begin by working the honey into the peanut butter.
Add powdered milk gradually
and
work
it in until it is of "play dough"
consistency.
Older
children can mix this themselves. Use rolling
pin,
cookie cutters, etc.
Children can eat this when they are finished.
Do not refrigerate.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt together.
Gradually add boiling water, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes; add remaining ingredients.
Serve hot over cake.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer at least 1 hour.
Serve in hamburger buns.

title: apricot oatmeal squares
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add butter or margarine.
In a 7 x 11-inch baking pan, pat about 2/3 of the crumb mixture.
On top, spread 1 (10 ounce) container of apricot pastry filling.
On top, sprinkle the remaining crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.
If desired, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: dirty pretzels
directions: Mix together oil, garlic powder, dill weed, lemon pepper and salad dressing mix in a bowl.
Pour into bag of broken pretzels and shake.
Turn bag to coat the pretzels.
Spread pretzels on cookie sheet and bake at 150° for about 1 hour.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Clean chicken breasts and dry well. In a shallow baking dish, combine the flour, cayenne pepper, paprika, salt and pepper. Dredge chicken breasts in flour mixture to coat. Shake off excess. In a large skillet, heat 1/4 inch vegetable oil over medium heat. Add chicken and brown well, about 2 minutes on each side. Remove from pan and set aside. Pour excess oil from pan, leaving a thin layer. Add onions and garlic, saute, stirring occasionally, until translucent, about 3 to 5 minutes. In a bowl, combine sour cream, chicken stock and green onions and mix well. Transfer chicken back to skillet, pour sour cream mixture over it. Bring to a simmer and cook, covered, until done, about 10 minutes.

title: fried catfish
directions: Mix together egg, mustard and hot sauce.
In another bowl, mix corn meal, flour and salt.
Dip fish in egg mixture, then dredge in corn meal mixture.
Fry in olive or canola oil for 2 - 3 minutes on each side.

title: philadelphia cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix sugar, egg yolks and cream cheese thoroughly.
Add margarine and flavoring; beat well.
Add flour slowly and beat for approximately 3 minutes.
Fold in beaten egg whites.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand about 6 hours in refrigerator before serving.
Rich and good.

title: spicy green tomato pie
directions: Combine tomatoes and apples sprinkled with lemon juice.
Place in pie shell.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves and ginger.
Cover top of pie with foil and bake in 375° oven 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and remove foil.
Return to oven and bake 30 minutes more.
Serve with warm cream.

title: cheese vegetable soup
directions: Cook vegetables in chicken broth until tender.
Add soup and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: gail's stew supreme
directions: In 6-quart crock-pot, layer meat and vegetables, alternately. Mix Season-All, paprika, cornstarch and tomato soup all together. Pour over ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook about 8 to 10 hours at low temperature.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, in oven.

Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over butter. Arrange pineapple slices on brown sugar; place cherry in center of each pineapple slice and arrange remaining cherries around slices. Press gently into brown sugar.
Add enough water to reserved pineapple juice to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Make cake mix as directed on package (omit water) using oil, eggs and the 1 1/4 cups pineapple juice mixture.
Pour batter over pineapple and cherries. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

Immediately run knife around side of pan to loosen cake and turn pan upside down onto heatproof serving plate; leave pan over cake 1 minute so brown sugar topping can drizzle over cake. Cool 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.
Store, loosely covered.

title: pork chops and dressing
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place browned pork chops in a baking dish. Mix bread, onion, eggs and enough water to moisten in a bowl. Heap bread mixture on top of pork chops.
Cover the dressing with the mushroom soup.
Bake for 30 minutes or until pork chops are done.

title: fresh peach roll
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Rub in with fingertips the butter.
Add enough milk to make a soft dough. Roll out in sheet form about 1/2-inch thick and dot with butter. Cover with sliced peaches; sprinkle with brown sugar and roll as a jelly roll.
Cut in uniform pieces about 2 1/2 or 3-inches wide. Place in buttered pan and pour the following sauce over same.

title: pumpkin nut roll
directions: Beat eggs on high mixer speed for 5 minutes, then gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir rest of the dry ingredients together, then fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with nuts; bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on kitchen towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll towel and cake together.
Cool 20 minutes; unroll.

title: cranberry pecan tassies
directions: Blend cheese and 1/2 cup butter. Stir in flour.
Chill 1 hour. Shape into 2 dozen (1-inch) balls.
Place in ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin pans.
Press dough evenly against bottom and sides of each.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil raisins 10 minutes and drain reserving 5 tablespoons raisin juice.
Add soda to 5 tablespoons raisin juice.
Mix remaining ingredients, adding nuts and raisins last.
Dip by spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: never fail sugar cookies
directions: Mix dry like a pie crust and then cut in shortening. Add remaining ingredients; roll out and cut. Cook 8 minutes.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix well and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: polish noodles and cabbage
directions: In a large skillet over moderate heat, melt butter.
Saute chopped onions for 2 minutes.
Add shredded cabbage, caraway seeds, salt and pepper.
Toss to mix and cook 5 to 8 minutes (or until cabbage is crisp-tender), stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, cook noodles in boiling salted water following package directions. Drain.
Toss with cabbage mixture.
Serve at once, piping hot. Good with meat loaf, pork chops or pork roast.
Very tasty with salmon loaf.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in given order.
Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in nonstick skillet or griddle at medium-high heat.
Drop mixture by large spoonfuls and flatten to pancake shape.
Brown on both sides.
Serve warm.
Makes a nice substitute for potatoes.

title: beef pot roast and noodles
directions: Lightly flour and brown roast in 2 tablespoons oil.
Put in Dutch oven or deep kettle; sprinkle with dry soup mix and pour can of soup over top, then 1 1/2 cans of water.
Cover and bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours until tender and falls apart.

title: fudge
directions: Mix chips, vanilla and butter in a large bowl and set aside. Heat sugar and milk in a double boiler and boil until that can't be stirred down.
Boil 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour boiling mixture over chips, vanilla and butter.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered cake pan.
Cut into squares when set.

title: no-cook icing
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add salt; beat.
Add sugar and beat until glossy.
Add Karo syrup and beat until it stands at a peak.
Spread on cake.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Put diced chicken over stuffing.
Add cream of chicken soup diluted with 1/2 can milk.
Pour 1 beaten egg over all.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grandma eichhorn's oatmeal cookies
directions: Add hot water over oatmeal until cookies are thin enough to drop on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and refrigerate.
Spread 1 cup of vanilla wafer crumbs in a large baking dish.
Whip chilled evaporated milk.
Add sugar and mix well.
Grate lemon rind and squeeze lemon for juice; add to mixture.
Add cooled jello and mix well.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Spread remaining cup of crumbs on top.
Chill for at least 3 hours.

title: new potatoes gruyere
directions: Cook potatoes in water until tender, along with onion and salt (set aside).
Mix last 4 ingredients in saucepan and heat slowly until thick.
Pour over hot potatoes and serve.
Yields 8 servings.

title: jelly roll
directions: Sift
flour,
baking
powder and salt; set aside.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon-colored.
Gradually beat in sugar, then blend
in water and vanilla.
Slowly mix in dry ingredients.
Pour into
a
jelly
roll pan (12 x 18-inch) which has been
lined with waxed paper or tinfoil and greased.
Bake at 375°
for
about 15
minutes
or
until
top
springs up when touched.
Loosen edges
and immediately turn upside down on a towel
sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Carefully remove paper and
then roll up while hot.
After cooling, unroll and spread with favorite filling or jelly and again roll up.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Cook sugar and syrup over medium heat for 3 or 4 minutes. Turn off.
Add rest of ingredients over popped corn.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Dissolve 1/4 cup sugar in lemon juice and water.
Cream remaining 1/2 cup sugar with butter until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Sift flour, measure and sift again with baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mix alternately with lemonade. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
When cookies cool, put 2 cookies together with Butter Frosting.

title: shrimp and pepper kabobs
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving tails intact.
Arrange in a large shallow dish.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Combine the softened cream cheese, mayonnaise, green onions or peppers, garlic powder and Tabasco sauce in a medium bowl.
Stir well. Add crabmeat and mix well. Cover and chill.

title: chocolate bavarian pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water until dissolved.
Add sugar and cocoa over heat and stirring until all granules dissolve.
Remove from heat.
Add 3/4 can of Pet milk and beat 5 minutes.
Chill until almost set.
Add remainder of Pet milk.
Pour into crust. Chill at least 1 1/2 hours.
When ready to serve, garnish with whipped cream and chocolate shavings.

title: sole wilshire
directions: Place thawed fish in well buttered dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle lemon juice and m.s.g.
In a separate bowl, mix chopped cucumber, onion and sour cream.
Add Tabasco, salt, pepper and thyme.
Spread over fish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Stir dry ingredients together in deep bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like crumbs.
Add buttermilk all at once and stir until mixture clings together.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick and cut.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: seven layer dinner
directions: Butter a large baking dish.
Layer the potatoes on the bottom. Cover with onions.
Cover onions with carrots.
Wash rice and sprinkle over carrots, then sprinkle generously with salt and pepper.
Pour can of peas over rice, then layer the sausage patties over all.
Pour soup over patties.
Bake, covered, in preheated 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels with rolling pin.
Mix pretzels, 4 tablespoons sugar and 3/4 cup of melted butter.
Pat into a
9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: gail's crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with electric mixer.
Blend in Lea and Perrins, lemon juice (can use ReaLemon), garlic powder and onion powder to taste.
Spread on pie plate or platter.
Cover with bottle of cocktail sauce and top with crab meat.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.
Add about 1/2 cup of mix to a mug of hot water.

title: jello jumble
directions: Mix well. Sprinkle 1 large box Jell-O ("any flavor") over mixture, dry. Mix well. Cover. Let stand about 3 hours before serving.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients and fold into cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: onion chicken(original recipe)
directions: Mix water and onion soup mix thoroughly and pour over chicken which has been placed in glass bowl large enough to accommodate chicken.
Turn chicken until mix thoroughly coats chicken. Marinate, covered, in refrigerator, turning occasionally for at least 6 hours (12 hours preferred).
Coat chicken with egg, dip into bread crumbs and fry very quickly in hot oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Great for party fare.

title: tropical fruit bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter a loaf pan.
Mash bananas.
Drain pineapple, chop and pat dry.
With electric mixer on low speed, beat flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt, eggs, bananas and butter until blended.
Increase speed to medium and beat 2 minutes.
Stir in pineapple and 1/2 cup coconut.
Pour into prepared pan and sprinkle with remaining 1 tablespoon coconut. Bake 1 hour (or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean).
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spice fruit punch
directions: Combine orange juice, pineapple juice, water and sugar.
Add grated rind of lemon, honey, cloves, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix and let stand 3 hours.
Strain through cheesecloth and add the ginger ale.
Stir briskly and serve in glasses containing ice cubes.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix flour and baking powder (really good), then cut in shortening. Add water. Knead, but not too much. Let dough set for a few minutes. Pinch off enough dough to form a small ball and flatten. You can make them as small or as big as you want. Drop into hot grease. Let each side brown; doesn't take long.

title: crab burgers
directions: Mix together and spread on cocktail bread or English muffins. Broil until hot and brown.

title: easy punch
directions: Set sherbet out of freezer to melt a little. Mix everything together in a punch bowl.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Make your favorite yellow cake mix.
While it is still warm, poke holes every half inch or so with a toothpick and pour condensed milk over the top.
Crush candy bars and pour the crumbs over the top of the cake.
Cover with cool whip after it cools.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a lightly greased lasagna pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight. The next morning, bake for one hour in a 350 degree oven. Serves: 10-12

title: dip for raw vegetables(low-fat)
directions: Mix well.
Let sit for 1 day in fridge.
Shake again.
Keeps well in fridge.

title: shrimp and sausage jambalaya
directions: On medium-high heat in large pot, heat oil.
Add sausage and cook until brown.
Remove sausage and drain off all but 2 tablespoons oil.
Add onions and green onions; saute until tender. Return sausage to pot.
Add shrimp and cook until they turn pink. Add rice, water, parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring water to a boil.
Cover pot and lower heat to simmer.
Cook until rice is tender.
Feeds an army.

title: 3-4-5 salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: all vegetable scalloped potatoes
directions: In a large buttered baking dish, mix all ingredients, except margarine. Salt and pepper to taste. Dot top of potatoes with margarine.
Sprinkle top with parsley. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Let stand until sugar has melted.
Add vanilla, oil and eggs; mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients; stir. Add nuts.
Mix and sprinkle butterscotch morsels over batter. Pour into oblong baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: l.b.j. beans
directions: Saute bacon until crisp.
Drain all but 3 tablespoons bacon fat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix together oatmeal and milk.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Set aside.
Beat until light and fluffy the brown sugar, eggs, shortening and vanilla.
Add baking powder, salt and soda.
Mix well into creamed mixture.
Add flour; mix.
Add oatmeal mixture and blend in well.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: bible cake
directions: Mix together and pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour pork(chinese; three parts)
directions: Mix well and set aside.

title: malaysian chicken breast
directions: Heat oil and saute chicken strips with garlic for 5 minutes. Add all other ingredients, except cornstarch.
Bring to a boil and add cornstarch to thicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over a bed of yellow rice.

title: barbecued clams
directions: Open raw clams.
Loosen all parts of clam from shell and keep on half shell.
Place in baking
pan that has 1 1/2 to 2-inch sides.
Place about 1/4 teaspoon of catsup on each clam. Next put 1/2-inch slice of cheese and top with 1/2-inch slice of bacon.
Broil until bacon is crisp, about 5 minutes.
Serve with crackers and a salad or may be used as an entree.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: potato or macaroni salad
directions: Cut up celery, onions and egg whites.
Mix egg yolks and mustard.
Add sugar, salad dressing, salt and vinegar.
Add milk.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to instructions on box.
After the cake has baked; make holes in the cake and pour the Eagle Brand milk and pina colada over the hot cake.
After it has cooled, spread Cool Whip over the cake and sprinkle it over with the coconut.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let chill, not solid.
Whip the cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Add to mixture.
Add marshmallows.
Put in refrigerator and let chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together and put in graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: vinegar and oil dressing
directions: A nice dish for breakfast is to have some mashed potatoes, make into nests, as many as your family numbers, break an egg in each nest, put in deep skillet, cover tightly and cook eggs until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Sift and measure 3 cups flour, then sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Cream eggs, oil and sugar.
Stir in zucchini.
Add sifted ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Add nuts.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: beef tips
directions: Cut roast into small pieces.
Put in a crock-pot and add Sprite, soup and water.
Cook on high for 4 to 6 hours.
To thicken, pour a can of beef gravy over and heat.
Serve over rice or cream potatoes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Place thawed Cool Whip in large bowl. Add dry pudding mix and marshmallows. Stir gently to blend. Add other ingredients and blend. Chill overnight.

title: silly putty
directions: Stir together; keep in covered container.

title: garden vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, saute the carrot, onion and garlic over low heat until softened, about 5 minutes.
Add broth, cabbage, tomato paste, basil, oregano, and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer, covered, about 15 minutes.
Stir in zucchini and heat 3 -4 minutes.

title: fish soup
directions: You can use the following fish:
squid, frog legs, lobster, goatfish, whitey, crabs and sandsharks.

title: sweet cornbread
directions: Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: cheese log
directions: Velveeta cheese and cream cheese need to be at room temperature.
Roll Velveeta cheese out to 1/4 inch thick between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Spread cream cheese on top.
Sprinkle with green chilies (drained), chopped pimientos (drained), and chopped olives (drained).

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
May be stored several weeks.
You can use date of sour cream as a guide.
It can be tinted for wedding, etc.

title: deviled ham and cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts.
Chill until slightly firm.
Form into desired shape and garnish with nuts and radish slices.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: spiceland methodist's mincemeat cake
directions: Mix ingredients well, as for any cake batter.
Pour into a lightly greased and lightly floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° until tests done (about 1 hour).
Wrap and let set for 24 hours. Then frost.
A cream cheese frosting is good.

title: bread and butter relishes
directions: Layer cucumbers and onions in gallon size container.
Combine remaining ingredients in a medium size pot.
Stir over low heat until sugar melts.
Let cool.
Place brine over cucumber and onion mix. Refrigerate for at least 1 week.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Pour half into a greased pan (tube pan or 13 x 9-inch pan).
Put apples on top of mixture in pan.
Sprinkle half of the sugar and cinnamon mixture over apples. Pour over remaining cake mixture.
Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours in tube pan or 45 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: dream bars
directions: Bake for 30 minutes in a slow oven (even a little longer is better).
Do not have the oven too hot.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Blend cake mix, jello, oil, nectar and eggs.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan for 1 hour or until done.
Bake in preheated 325° oven.

title: mexican dip
directions: Remove paper and mash tamales; add chili and melted cheese. Serve in heated fondue pot with assorted chips.

title: summer squash and onions
directions: In a large skillet, melt the butter over low heat.
Add the squash and onion; mix thoroughly and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the salt, pepper, tomato juice and sugar.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat for 15 minutes, or until the squash and onion are tender.
Uncover to stir several times during cooking.
Serves 4.

title: wheat germ cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine dry cake mix, egg, brown sugar, oil, butter, wheat germ and water in a bowl.
Mix with spoon; dough will be stiff.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes for chewy cookies, 12 minutes for crispy cookies.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: citrus mint cooler
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cover; remove from heat and let steep until cool.
Strain.
Cover and refrigerate.
To serve, fill glasses or pitcher with equal amounts of fruit juice, ginger ale and water.
Add ice and serve immediately.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: "mom's christmastime punch"
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: grilled pork a l'orange
directions: Trim pork chops well.
Broil or grill until nearly done (7 to 10 minutes on each side).
Combine other ingredients and pour half of the mixture over chops.
Broil or grill 2 minutes more.
Turn and pour remaining sauce on other side.
Broil or grill 2 minutes more.
Serve.
Garnish with an orange slice.
Yield: 4 servings. Serving Size: 1 chop.
Per serving: Calories: 241, Fat: 9 g, Sodium: 115 mg.
Exchanges per serving:
3 lean meat, 1 starch/bread.

title: ruby french salad dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients and shake well.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Just mix yeast in 2 1/2 cups of very warm water; let set. Beat eggs, sugar, shortening and salt, then add water mixture. Beat well, then add flour, 1 1/2 cups at a time.
Mix well.

title: smoky salmon spread
directions: Drain salmon.
Reserve 2 teaspoons salmon liquid.
Flake salmon.
Combine cream cheese, liquid smoke flavoring and salmon liquid.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in green onions.
Fold in salmon. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours to blend flavors.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: In large bowl with mixer at medium speed (or spoon), beat all ingredients until very smooth, adding milk if necessary to make good spreading consistency.
Frosts 1 (2 layer) cake or 1 (9 x 13-inch) cake or 1 tube cake or 2 dozen cupcakes.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and sugar in a large mixing bowl. Add drained pineapple, strawberries (juice and all) and sliced bananas.
Fold in whipped topping.
Freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Keep frozen.
Slice and serve.

title: italian sausage
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly in a bowl.
Cover and let sit in refrigerator overnight; do not freeze.
Next day, form into 4 patties and fry or use in combination with other recipes.
Yields 4 servings.
Serving size:
one 3-ounce patty.

title: greek grape salad
directions: Toss all ingredients in small bowl.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mom's best chocolate cake
directions: Mix together the sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla and melted chocolate.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Alternate flour mixture and water into sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla and chocolate.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: loose meat hamburger
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Add 1/3 cup of dry mixture to ground beef and water.
Cook, uncovered, until water cooks away.
Serve on buns.
Add onions and pickles, if desired.

title: western skillet casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat.
Add soup mix, water, rice and tomatoes.
Simmer, covered, 25 minutes or until water is absorbed and rice is tender.
Add peas (drained); simmer 5 minutes more. Put mixture in casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° to melt cheese.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Rub baking dish with butter and crushed garlic.
