Put in layer of sliced potatoes and cover with shredded Gruyere cheese; another layer of potatoes and cheese.
Then pour over a can of chicken stock and bake.

title: strawberries supreme
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water and juice of frozen berries (thawed).
Let jello cool, not jell.
Add berries and Cool Whip.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in 8-inch square dish.
Combine flour, cheese and seasonings in a plastic bag.
Place sliced potatoes in the bag and shake.
Lay coated potatoes in melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning potatoes once.

title: enchilada soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in a small amount of butter.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour, covered.
Add 3 cups grated Cheddar cheese and 6 corn tortillas cut into strips. Cook uncovered for 10 minutes.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: shredded wheat bread
directions: Pour boiling
water
over Shredded Wheat biscuits.
Add salt, granulated sugar, molasses and shortening.	Let Shredded Wheat, water,
salt,
sugar,
molasses
and shortening cool to lukewarm and add
yeast in warm water.
Mix thoroughly and add flour.
Let rise double in bulk.
Shape in 2 loaves; let rise. Bake at 400° the first 15 minutes, then at 350° for remaining time, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix well
together
the
cream cheese and 1 cup of milk until smooth.
Add instant pie filling and remainder of milk. After blending
well, place on graham crust and put in refrigerator to chill.
You can then put cherry pie filling on top, if desired.

title: halirbsi-stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook rice halfway (not done) and let cool.
Core and separate leaves from cabbage in hot water.
Remove any hard stems.
Add meat, onions and salt and pepper to rice mixture.
(Mushrooms may also be added, if desired.)
Put mixture on leaves and wrap loosely but securely.
Put in cooking pot.
Pour boiling water over the rolls carefully and simmer slowly until tender.
Tomato sauce or canned tomatoes can be substituted for boiling water or serve with tomato sauce, gravy or catsup.

title: tuna twirls
directions: *Put egg into cup and add enough milk to equal 3/4 cup.

title: cheesy buttons
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix and butter.
Stir in water and sesame seed until dough forms ball.
Drop by scant teaspoons into cheese (shape half into ovals if desired).
Coat dough with cheese.
Place about 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until golden, 7 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields about 3 dozen appetizers.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Sift flour and sugar 3 times.
You can add 2 teaspoons boiling water for a creamier texture.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter a 2-quart baking dish.
Scald milk with butter and sugar.
Beat eggs; add salt and vanilla when milk is cool.
Stir in egg mixture.
Pour over bread in baking dish.
Set dish in pan of water and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: play dough
directions: In a heavy pan, mix dry ingredients.
Add water and oil.
Cook mixture over medium-high to high heat for 3 minutes (stirring). Cool and knead.
Store in airtight container.

title: california chicken
directions: Sprinkle onion soup mix over bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle rice evenly over soup mix.
Lay chicken on top of rice.
Dilute mushroom soup with water and pour over chicken. Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry buckle
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg and vanilla, then milk.
In separate bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Stir into liquid mixture. Fold in berries.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Blend together tomatoes and both soups.
Cook, salt, debone and dice chicken.
Layer in a baking pan chicken, crushed Doritos, soup mix and sliced Velveeta cheese.
Bake 15 minutes in a 275° oven.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute large onion in butter; do not brown.
Keep in liquid. Add brandy (or beer) when pan is hot.
Heat broth and add onions with liquid.
Add sweet vermouth.
Top with croutons and Parmesan cheese.

title: cheezy nacho beef dinner
directions: Saut rice mix and ground beef until beef is browned.
Stir in water, salsa, corn, beans and Rice-A-Roni seasoning mix.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to low heat; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in chopped tomatoes.
Serve with cheese, sour cream and tortilla chips.

title: maida's tuna treats
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the cheese.
Press into 12 buttered muffin tins.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt together; mix well. Add vanilla, oil and vinegar; mix well.
Pour 2 cups water over ingredients and mix well with electric mixer or hand.
Bake in any size pan in a 375° oven for 40 minutes or until done (check with a toothpick).

title: connie's carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and blend well. Bake at 350° in tube pan for 30 minutes.

title: dumplings(makes 3 dozen dumplings)
directions: Bring to a boil the first 3 ingredients.
Add flour all at one time.
Beat with a wooden spoon until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a smooth ball.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 eggs, 1 at a time, beat until smooth after each addition.
Heat to boiling in a large saucepan the 2-quarts water and salt.
Drop dumplings by rounded teaspoonfuls into water.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, until dumplings rise to surface of water.
Place over stews or soup.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain and clean salmon; mix everything.
Chill; roll in chopped walnuts.
Great to mix a day ahead.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in hot oil.
Add garlic and cook until yellow. Add soy sauce, salt and 1/2 cup water to steak.
Cook 25 minutes. Add green pepper, onion and celery to mixture.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Blend cornstarch with 1 cup water and stir into mixture. Add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes more.
Serve hot over cooked rice.

title: best of all fruit salad
directions: Dice apples; add lemon juice.
Cut pineapple in small pieces. Mix fruit, walnuts and marshmallows.
Serve with dressing.

title: boiled rice pudding
directions: Stir a small amount of rice mix into this and then mix into the rice.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.

title: hello dolly pie
directions: Mix the chocolate chips, coconut, graham cracker cracker crumbs, pecans and sweetened condensed milk together, then pour in melted butter.
Put into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for about 35 minutes.

title: quick nachos
directions: Place tortilla chips on paper plate.
Sprinkle with cheese. Shake Tabasco vinegar lightly over cheese, just the juice of the peppers.
Place in microwave on High for 30 seconds, until cheese is melted, then serve.

title: pork roast
directions: Mix all ingredients except roast.
Put roast in container and cover with marinade.
Let set 2 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Put on grill and brown or cook on all sides about 20 minutes.
Cook in slow cooker on low about 3 to 4 hours.
Can also be cooked in oven.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes; wash
and
grate
fine.
Drain.
Add egg yolks, flour, salt
and
onions.
Fold
in
stiffly beaten egg whites; mix well.
Spoon
on
a griddle that has been greased, or a large frypan that has been greased.
Brown on both sides. Make cakes thin.
Serves 5 to 7.

title: korean barbecued beef with broccoli
directions: Trim fat from beef; cut beef diagonally across grain
into 1/8-inch slices (for ease in cutting, partially freeze beef about 1 1/2 hours).
Mix remaining ingredients (except broccoli); stir in beef until well coated.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Drain beef, reserving liquid.
Stir-fry beef in wok 2 to 3 minutes or until brown.
Remove beef.
Stir-fry broccoli for 1 to 2 minutes, then add reserved liquid and continue to stir-fry until liquid boils and broccoli is tender-crisp.
Add beef to wok to warm.
Serve beef and broccoli mixture over rice.

title: beef stew
directions: Cube beef and saute in small amount of oil.
Place beef, sliced onions, carrots and tomatoes in a crock-pot.
Add water and spices.
Cook for 2 hours. Add potatoes that have been quartered. Continue cooking until tender.

title: cheese boat
directions: Cube Velveeta and put with mayonnaise in a double boiler or microwave dish and melt.
Be careful not to scorch.
If seems too thick, add a little milk.
Add seasonings to taste.
Put as much as you think you'll need, then double it (flavor gets lost in Velveeta).
Hollow out bread to make a boat, then cube bread for dipping.
Put boat and cubes on cookie sheet and fill with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until browning.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order, being sure that the shortening is added last.
Chill dough in refrigerator.
Roll 1/2 teaspoon of dough in your hand into a small ball, then roll in granulated sugar.
Bake on greased sheet in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: turkey chile
directions: Saute turkey, onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, cinnamon, ground coriander, salt, wine, beans (undrained) and tomato sauce.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bring cream, butter and sugar to a full boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add liqueur and chocolate; stir until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Chill until firm enough to handle, about 3 1/2 hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in cocoa, coconut or nuts.
Store covered in refrigerator. Makes 2 dozen candies.

title: country-style chili
directions: Brown the meat.
Add onions and peppers, cook.
Dump in the tomatoes and cook until saucy.
Mix everything else in.
Cook over medium-low heat.
Add chili powder to taste.

title: turnip puff
directions: Mash turnips.
Combine other ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour in 375° oven.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in order in clear bowl:
lettuce, celery, green pepper, onion, frozen peas, bacon, eggs, mayonnaise and Cheddar cheese on top.
Cover and let set overnight.

title: pumpkin surprise
directions: Mix sugar, salt and spices; add beaten eggs, milk and pumpkin. Mix and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sift cake mix evenly over top.
Dribble melted butter over top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: party chex
directions: Mix together the cereal, nuts and pretzels.
Melt the white chocolate chips with the oil over lowest heat.
Pour this evenly over the dry mixture.
Place in a pan and freeze firm.
Then break apart mixture and place into a serving container.

title: cauliflower broccoli salad
directions: Brown bacon; drain and set aside.
Clean and cut up cauliflower and broccoli.
Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Pour over vegetables and add bacon; mix well. Mix together only about 2 hours before serving.

title: finch frils(pet)
directions: Save tuna or cat food cans.
Recipe makes 4 cans.
Spoon into cans a combination of millet, bread crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle with grit.
Put suet through meat grinder, then melt down in double boiler.
Let set to slightly harden, then reheat.
Pour over ingredients in cans until can is full.
Refrigerate to harden.
Nail to tree with 6-inch nail; tape exposed part of nail to make safe perch.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together and pour into hot iron skillet, well-greased. Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.

title: corned beef salad mold
directions: Soften jello in hot water.
Add salt and chill until partially set.
Add other ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold to chill.
Be sure to grease mold with mayonnaise. Serve with your favorite crackers.
Bundt pan makes nice mold but would need to be doubled.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in milk, butter, nutmeg and vanilla; pour into dry ingredients and mix well.
Fold into berries.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: caramel corn
directions: Heat the first four ingredients on stove and scorch (not too much).
Add soda and, while it foams, pour it over popped popcorn. Let cool.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and cook until brown.
Will rise to top of oil, turn and brown other side.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix the milk with pudding and stir until thick.
Mix Cool Whip with cream cheese and sugar.
Add pudding to the Cool Whip and cream cheese mixture.
Stir well.
Crumble cookies in bottom of pan.
Add layer of pudding and repeat another layer of cookies and pudding.
Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and heat.
This will make baking much easier.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix the cooking oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift and add the flour, salt and soda.
Fold in chopped pecans (according to taste)
and raw apples.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
When cake is done, make Sauce Topping.

title: zucchini frittata
directions: To eggs, add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch well-greased Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Cut in slices like bread, then cut each slice into 3 or 4 pieces.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 25 small pieces.

title: strawberry salad(club member: ben steadman)
directions: Combine pretzels, butter and sugar. Put in 9 x 12-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Let cool. Cream sugars and cream cheese. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread over pretzel crust. Seal around edges. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add strawberries. Let cool, but not gel. Pour over cream cheese layer. Chill at least 1 hour! Delicious salad or dessert!

title: marinated macaroni salad
directions: Cook
and
drain macaroni.
Combine first 6 ingredients in a large
salad bowl.
Mix sugar and vinegar in a saucepan. Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add milk and mayonnaise.
Pour over macaroni mixture.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda.
Mix water and mayonnaise.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add flavoring; stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 well greased and floured pans.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook and season chicken.
Save 1 1/2 quarts broth.
Cook spaghetti in broth and drain, but do not rinse.
Save broth and add to mixture later.
Saute pepper and onion in butter.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire, mushrooms and cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese melts.
Add spaghetti and chicken.
Place in casserole.
Cook at 350° until mixture bubbles.
May be prepared day ahead.
Freezes well.

title: strata breakfast cups
directions: Line cupcake pans with liners.
Spray liners with Pam baking spray.
Fill cups 3/4 full with bread cubes.
Place a spoonful of bacon or sausage over bread.
Pour beaten egg and milk mixture over bread until bread is saturated.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: lemon-lime pineapple punch
directions: Mix ingredients.
Yield is little over a gallon.
Freeze punch in ice trays for ice.

title: chocolate fudge cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Prepare chocolate crumb crust.
Beat cheese until fluffy in large mixer bowl.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Chill.
(Refrigerate.)

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Spread 1/2 stick of butter (melted) in dish.
Pour in batter, pour fruit with juice on top.
Bake at 350° until done.
Batter will rise to top and brown when done.

title: feather light pancakes
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. With fork, mix ingredients to evenly blend.
In a separate container, mix eggs, milk, bacon drippings and sour cream. Combine liquids with dry ingredients, blending until smooth.
Do not overbeat.

title: psychedelic pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter together; add sugar, then eggs. Sift flour and baking powder together and add to batter alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Mix batter well.
Separate batter into 3 bowls.
Color each bowl desired colors.
Grease and flour large tube pan.
Pour colored batter alternately into pan; set in cold oven and set at 375° and cook for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and cook for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: sweet-sour sausage appetizer
directions: Brown sausage in medium skillet over medium heat; drain on paper towels.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in a medium saucepan. Add reserved pineapple juice and soy sauce; stir until well blended.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add vinegar, pineapple, green pepper and sausage. Heat until hot.
Serve in a chafing dish.
Makes about 36 pieces.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour, cream of tartar and soda.
Alternate, adding flour and buttermilk mixture to butter mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon flavoring, nuts and cherries.
Bake at 350° in 3 (9-inch) pans for 25 minutes.

title: king's cake
directions: Cream the fat and gradually add sugar and vanilla sugar, the eggs and the flavoring.
Mix and sieve the flour and the baking powder to the creamed mixture; add milk.
The consistency should be firm, do not use too much milk.
Fold in the washed raisins and candied lemon peel.
Grease an oblong cake tin and line with paper.
Fill the mixture into the prepared tin.
Place low in the oven.
Bake in moderate oven (375° to 400°) for 80 to 100 minutes.

title: lemon delight pie
directions: Prepare filling mix as directed on package for pie.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Measure 1 cup filling into a bowl.
Place plastic wrap directly on surface and cool thoroughly. Pour remaining filling into pie shell.
Chill.
Stir cooled filling until smooth.
Blend in 2 cups whipped topping.
Spoon over filling in pie shell.
Chill 3 hours.
Garnish with additional topping and lemon slices, if desired.

title: best brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and melted chocolate.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy peanut butter crumb cake
directions: Add baking soda to boiling water, mix and let cool.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and water to creamed mixture and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa.
Fold flour mixture and peanut butter chips into sugar and shortening.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar, chocolate chips and walnuts together.
Sprinkle on the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine; add eggs and buttermilk.
Then add sifted dry ingredients.
Lastly, add bananas and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: china curled shrimp
directions: Wash and drain the shrimp.
Sprinkle with the salt and pepper. Heat the oil in a skillet; saute the shrimp 1 minute.
Add a mixture of the ketchup, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, ginger, scallions and garlic.
Cook over low heat 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Mix together the cornstarch and water.
Add to the shrimp and cook 2 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Brown beef and cook onion until tender.
Pour off fat.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pans.
Cover with top crust and seal edges.
Slit top.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: bev's brunswick stew
directions: Stir during cooking (several hours until thick), mashing vegetables lightly.
Serve with corn bread, cole slaw and hot apple with pie with Cheddar cheese wedge.
Serves 8.

title: country breakfast casserole
directions: Steam broccoli and set aside.
Saute peppers and onions in butter and set aside.
Beat eggs in small bowl.
Add milk to eggs and mix well.
Spread potato slices in 15 x 10 inch baking dish. Spread broccoli over potatoes and sprinkle evenly with ham.
Layer pepper and onions over ham and season with salt and pepper. Spread cheeses over the top of the casserole.
Pour egg and milk mixture over cheeses.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 60 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: irish coffee
directions: Fill coffee mug with hot strong coffee.
Add brown sugar and whiskey.
Stir.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Use baked sweet potatoes.
Cream sugar with thoroughly softened margarine and eggs, one at a time.
Add sweet potatoes, milk, flour, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into crusts and bake approximately 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crab casserole or deviled crab
directions: Mix all ingredients well and beat in hot water.
Place in a greased casserole dish or crab shells.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until lightly brown. Serves 5 or 6.

title: baked broccoli casserole
directions: Put cooked broccoli in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with the Velveeta cheese.
Combine Carnation milk and mushroom soup and pour over Velveeta.
Bake 25 minutes.
The last 5 minutes sprinkle with onion rings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in 3/4-inch slices.
Dip into egg, then into bread crumbs, then carefully into egg and bread crumbs again. Melt butter in large skillet.
Add green tomatoes slices and cook slowly until golden brown on each side and tomato is tender. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine sliced
(1/4-inch)
cucumbers

and onions. Sprinkle generously (1/2 cup) with canning salt. Let stand 1 hour. Drain off salt water. Put plenty of ice cubes over cukes and onions and let stand 1 hour. Drain off water. Combine with other ingredients. Mix well. Bring to a simmer and simmer 2 minutes. Avoid boiling (it softens the slices). Pack in sterilized jars.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet; drain off excess fat.
Add taco mix and water.
Simmer, uncovered, until mixture is thickened, about 15 minutes.
Lightly grease bottom of an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Spread refried beans evenly on the bottom. Sprinkle with shredded lettuce, onions and chilies; top with ground beef mixture. (If desired, cover and refrigerate until ready to finish.)
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with shredded cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Remove from oven and garnish sides with tortilla chips.
Serve with chopped tomato, sliced olives, sour cream and taco sauce in separate serving dishes.

title: barbecue mayo
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill.
Yields 1 cup.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove skin and bones.
Separate into flakes.
Mix first 7 ingredients into salmon.
Add egg yolks well beaten.
Fold in 3 egg whites stiffly beaten.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 320° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, stir all ingredients together until well mixed.
Drop from teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until center of cookies are golden brown.
Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute, then remove to rack to finish cooling.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together very good.
(May sift all before mixing.) Makes 1 gallon of milk.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and pat out.
Fry in oil until brown.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender; drain liquid.
Mix celery, salad dressing, onions and cheese.
Spread over vegetables.
Mix butter and crackers.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Line a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with waxed paper; set aside.
To make frosting, in a bowl beat butter.
Add cocoa powder.
Beat in 1/4 cup of the milk.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until combined.
Beat in remaining 1/4 cup milk and the vanilla until combined.

title: indian fry bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, add 4 cups flour, unsifted.
Add baking powder, baking soda, salt and mix thoroughly.
Add 2 cups warm water, 1 cup at a time, until mixture becomes sticky.
Use remaining cup of flour in two parts, 1/2 cup to knead the dough and 1/2 cup to roll dough out.

title: grandmother louise's italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry sausage until well browned and cooked through.
Remove sausage; fry tomato paste in sausage drippings.
Fry until dark. Add garlic, oregano and bay leaf.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Add canned tomatoes; stir well, then add sausage.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours, or as long as you like.
This recipe comes from Northern Italy.

title: layer salad
directions: Place ingredients in order given in salad bowl.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: peking shrimp
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in a large frying pan.
Mix and heat.
When it begins to thicken, add shrimp, tomato and pepper. Heat through and serve over rice.
Serves two.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Freeze.

title: bridal punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in hot water. Add cold water and stir. When served, add 2 liter ginger ale.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine all thawed vegetables, soup, sour cream, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 can of the onions.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover dish and add remaining cheese and onions; bake for an extra 5 minutes.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomatoes together.
Form balls out of mixture and place in baking dish.
Pour crushed tomatoes with juice over balls.
Bake in oven 45 minutes at 400°.

title: helen's special congealed salad(heritage)
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water and pineapple juice.
Mash cream cheese with mayonnaise and add milk.
Add cream cheese mixture to Jell-O and congeal slightly before adding pineapple, mixed with lemon juice, pecans and celery.
Congeal overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: nelda machovsky's fruit slush mix
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add orange juice concentrate, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Fill 6 or 7 ice cube trays with mixture.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from trays and store in plastic bags.
Use within 6 months.
Fill glass with fruit slush mix cubes.
Add ginger ale to cover.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Stir and serve. (Makes approximately 100 small ice cubes.)

title: georgie's sandwiches
directions: Mix together.
Spread on party rye and broil until bubbly all over.

title: chicken-vegetable stir-fry
directions: Stir cornstarch,
ginger, broth and soy sauce until smooth. Set aside.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Stir-fry chicken until brown.
Remove; set aside.
Place remaining 1 tablespoon oil in skillet.
Heat.
Stir-fry vegetables with garlic until tender-crisp.
Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in reserved chicken and broth.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: cream cheese pecan pie
directions: In the large bowl of an electric mixer, at medium speed, beat together until smooth the cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/3 cup light brown sugar and 1 teaspoon maple flavoring.
Spread over the bottom of the pastry shell.
Sprinkle with the pecans.
In the clean large bowl of the mixer, at medium speed, beat the remaining 3 eggs until frothy.
Add the corn syrup, 1/4 cup light brown sugar, salt and 1 teaspoon maple flavoring; beat until blended.
Gently pour the mixture over the pecans.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven until a knife inserted halfway between the center and edge comes out clean, 40 minutes.
Place on wire rack to cool before cutting. Makes 10 servings.

title: will's tomato-cheddar spread
directions: Stir in large bowl the Ro-Tel, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and salt. Then stir in Cheddar cheese and pimento.
Serve with crackers or Frito Scoops.

title: squash pickles
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in large pan; set aside 1 hour, then drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and bell pepper in a large pan and bring to a hard boil.
Add squash mixture.
Bring to a boil, then put in pint jars.
Put jars in canner with water almost to top of jars.
When water starts to simmer, let jars set for 5 minutes.
Make sure jars seal.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar to Cool Whip, stir well (I whip).
Add to peanut butter and cream cheese mixture. Whip well and pour into crust.
(If too stiff, add a little milk.) Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: cheeseburger soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine water, carrots, onion, beef bouillon, potatoes, green pepper, garlic and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Brown beef and drain.
Stir in beef and 2 cups milk.
Heat through.

title: mushroom stuffed chicken roll(serves 6; 305 calories per roll)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine celery, mushrooms, bread crumbs, ham, parsley, basil and salt.
Mix well.
Add 4 tablespoons melted margarine and toss.
Spoon about 2 1/2 tablespoons of mushroom stuffing in the center of each chicken breast.
Roll up and secure each with toothpicks.
Fry chicken rolls in remaining 3 tablespoons margarine for 10 minutes. Transfer chicken rolls into baking dish and spoon in remaining stuffing.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pork and peppers pasta
directions: Stir-fry pork and garlic in oil in 2-quart saucepan.
Remove from pan.
In same pan, prepare pasta and cheese as directed on package, except omitting margarine and adding pork and remaining ingredients during last 3 minutes of cooking.
Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 8 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients together at medium speed.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add celery, pepper, tomatoes, sauce, salt and herbs.
Add beans last.
Simmer for 20 minutes and pour into oblong baking pan.
Drizzle thin cornmeal mixture over top and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
A salad is all you need to add for a complete meal.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add alternately with pumpkin.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour into ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pudding by theresa
directions: Mix over medium flame the sugar, flour, eggs and milk until thick.
Add vanilla.

title: spinach-avocado-orange toss
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake until thoroughly blended.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl and pour the dressing over all.
Toss lightly.
Yield:
10 servings. Approximate calories/serving:

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 package of coconut.
Mix until blended.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
After cake cools, put 2 cups milk, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 cup sugar in saucepan and get hot, but not to boiling point.
Pour over cool cake after punching holes over the top with a fork.
Let cool.
Put Cool Whip on top of cake and add remaining coconut over top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: eclair
directions: Place 1 package of graham crackers on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan or round cupcake carrier.
Mix milk and pudding.
Add Cool Whip. Pour 1/2 mixture on top of crackers.
Place second layer of crackers on top, then add rest of pudding mixture.
Place third layer of crackers on top.
Refrigerate until firm.
Top with frosting.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together beans and soup.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Take out and sprinkle with onion rings.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; add taco seasoning as directed on package.
On plates, layer Doritos, beef, sour cream, tomatoes and cheese, then lettuce.
Start small, it grows.

title: meat loaf(sweet and delicious!)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a loaf. Place in baking dish. May garnish top with 3 tablespoons each: mustard, brown sugar and ketchup, mixed together, last 15 minutes in oven. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: amaretto hot fruit compote
directions: Drain fruits reserving syrup for other uses.
Combine canned fruits in a large bowl and set aside.
Combine bananas and lemon juice.
Toss gently and add to fruit mix.
Layer 1/2 each of fruit mix and macaroon crumbs in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons of almonds.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter. Repeat.
Pour Amaretto evenly over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining almonds.
Stir before serving. Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: maryland flounder("lo-cal")
directions: Wrap fillets around cherry tomatoes.
Poach flounder fillets in chicken broth and wine for 10 minutes or until they just begin to flake when tested with a fork.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients on fillets.
Serve with lemon wedges and sprinkle with paprika. Serves 4.

title: "quick" steak preparation
directions: Pound steak and dredge with flour, salt and pepper.
Minute steak may be used.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar and spices. Combine with the pumpkin, eggs and milk. Pour into a 10-inch pastry shell.
Place pecan halves around the edge.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes and then reduce heat to 350° and bake for an additional 40 minutes.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans in water for four hours.
Drain and rinse beans. Saute onion in butter for 3 minutes until softened.
Add and saute celery another 3 minutes; add beans, bay leaf, thyme, parsley and broth.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Discard bay leaf and parsley sprigs.
Puree half the mixture in the blender. Return puree to the saucepan containing remainder of soup.
Heat to simmering point and lemon juice and sherry.

title: easy chicken saute
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, thickly slice mushrooms and zucchini.
Chop onion.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat in 1 tablespoon hot oil, cook zucchini until tender-crisp and lightly browned.
Remove to plate.
In same skillet in 1 more tablespoon hot oil, cook mushrooms until browned.
Remove to bowl.

title: seashell salad
directions: Mix together last four ingredients.
Set aside.

title: apple crisp pie
directions: Pour apples into 9-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix cake mix with sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle this over fruit.
Dot pats of butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can double recipe to use whole cake mix (use 9 x 17-inch casserole dish).

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain liquid off of beans, peas and pimentos.
Mix vinegar, oil and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Let marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Drain off liquid before serving.
Serve cold.

title: autumn salad
directions: Heat pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Boil for 3 minutes. Add dry Jell-O; stir.
Add cream cheese.
Stir this in.
Cool. Add celery, apples and nuts.
Stir in.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in 9-inch square dish.
Chill.
Cut in squares.

title: oriental marmalade
directions: Cut up apricots, figs, dates and raisins.
Cover with cold water.
Soak overnight.
Add sugar and juice from lemons.
Cook slowly until thick, about 40 minutes.
Pour into sterilized glasses.
Seal with paraffin.

title: cappuccino
directions: Mix all
ingredients,
except for the whipped cream and cinnamon stick, in	a
saucepan.
Bring
to a boil.
Pour into cups and top
with	whipped cream and cinnamon stick. Yields 4 servings.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients in order as listed and pour in unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle nutmeg on top of pie before baking. Bake at 350° until done. Pie is done when you stick knife in it and it comes out clean.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Boil spaghetti in broth. Add all ingredients; mix well.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dave's pork chops
directions: Chop all peppers, mushrooms and onions into approximately 2-inch square pieces and place in large pot, add butter or margarine.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease one 9 x 12-inch cake pan per four chops.
Shake-N-Bake all chops and place in pan(s).
Cover all chops with sliced tomatoes.
Place pot with chopped vegetables on medium heat, simmer, cover and stir occasionally.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Place pans with chops in oven and cook a total of one hour.
When chops are 15 minutes from being done, pour vegetable mixture over each pan of chops, making sure that the sauce and vegetables are equally distributed.
Remove dish at one hour and eat.

title: mushroom mousse
directions: Melt butter over moderate heat.
Add shallots and cook for about 1 minute.
Add mushrooms, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook for about 5 minutes, until mushrooms have released their juices. Raise heat to high; cook until mixture is almost dry, about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.

title: russ' potatoes
directions: Cube potatoes and boil until tender, about 25 minutes.
Saute onions in olive oil, using nonstick pan.
Make sure onions are well browned.
Mash potatoes and stir in onions and horseradish. Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Use paper towels to blot extra liquid.
Spinach must be very dry.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.
Let stand 12 hours before serving.
Good with vegetables or thick crusty bread.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine corn and milk; heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into a 6 x 10-inch greased baking dish.
If desired, top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: waverlies
directions: Bring to boil the margarine, butter and sugar for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Have cookie sheet lined with Waverly crackers and quickly drizzle mixture over crackers.
Work quickly.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 300°.
Watch closely and do not burn.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Chop apples and mix with sugar.
Set aside for 30 minutes. Add Mazola oil, eggs, flour, cinnamon, soda, salt and vanilla. Mix well.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake at 350°
about 1 hour and 10 minutes in Bundt pan.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salt water until tender. Peel and slice potatoes.
In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Reserve 1/4 cup drippings.
Cook onion and celery in drippings until tender but not brown. Stir in the flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper. Add water and vinegar.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in bacon and potatoes. Cook about 5 minutes or until heated through, tossing lightly.
Add hard-boiled eggs. Toss lightly just to mix.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy mexican dip
directions: On a plate, spread bean dip in a 7-inch circle.
In even layers, top with chiles, then avocado dip, then olives.
Sprinkle on eggs, then cheese.
Invert a large bowl over all and chill until ready to serve.
Top with tomato before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips or sliced zucchini and carrots.

title: root vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the butter and slowly cook the onions, shallots, leeks and garlic until tender and soft, about 5 minutes.
Do not brown.
Add the diced root vegetables and stock. Simmer until all vegetables are soft, approximately 35 minutes. Puree in 2-cup batches in a food processor until smooth.

title: mushroom-romaine salad
directions: Break romaine into salad bowl.
Add sliced mushrooms and scallions.
Blend oil, vinegar, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add to salad and toss just before serving.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice); heat juice, vinegar, sugar and egg and add flour.
Stir until thick; add apples, pineapple and peanuts and stir in marshmallows.
Chill 1 hour.
Add Cool Whip and chill until ready to serve.

title: lettuce slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: linda marrow's sad cake
directions: Take Bisquick, eggs, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat all this stuff up.
Dump in chopped pecans and coconut.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
If they don't fall, shake them until they do.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix cheese and sugar; spread on crust.
Add Cool Whip, now nuts.
Spoon pie filling on top.
Chill overnight.

title: chicken sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients together except poppy seed with mixer on low speed.
After blended, stir in poppy seed and pour in pint jar and refrigerate.
Serve on chicken sandwiches or use as dip for chicken.
Will last up to 4 weeks in refrigerator.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift
flour with
cup
sugar four times.
Beat egg whites with
salt
until frothy; add cream of tartar and beat until stiff,
but not dry.
Add remaining sugar, 1 tablespoon at
a time,
folding
in
thoroughly.
Add
vanilla with last addition of sugar.
Sift flour mixture over top a little at a time
and fold in lightly with a down-up-over motion.
Bake in 10-inch ungreased angel
cake pan in moderate oven at 325° for 75 minutes. Invert pan to cool.

title: vegetable cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/4 of the stuffing mix. Spoon into lightly greased 5-quart casserole.
Top with reserved stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter snack
directions: Mix and heat margarine, peanut butter and chips. Pour over cereals, mixed. Pour powdered sugar into a paper bag, then add cereal. Shake bag until cereal is coated with sugar.

title: fried rice(japanese)
directions: Put wok or pan on high heat, add oil. Whisk eggs in a small bowl. Put the eggs in the heated pan and scramble very quickly. Stop the heat and remove the scrambled eggs from the pan into a dish. Put the pan back on high heat and add more oil. Saute the vegetables and chicken until soft. Add garlic salt and chicken bouillon. Add rice and stir well. Add the scrambled egg to the rice mixture and mix together. Turn the heat to low, add soy sauce and stir quickly. Remove form heat and serve right away.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers paper thin into a bowl.
Salt layers generously.
Add onion, sliced thinly.
Cover bowl and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Remove bowl 10 minutes before serving.
Shake covered bowl and drain salted water by squeezing with hands.
Combine vinegar, sour cream, sugar and pepper.
Pour over cucumbers and return to refrigerator until ready to serve.
More sugar may be added, if necessary.
Serves 4.

title: microwave beef stew
directions: In 4-quart casserole dish, combine 1 1/2 cups water, soup mix, bay leaf, carrots and cubed potatoes.
Heat, covered, 7 to 8 minutes on High.
Continue cooking on power level 3, Medium-low, an additional 50 to 52 minutes, until beef, carrots and potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add peas and flour, blended with remaining water.
Heat 6 to 8 minutes on Medium-low until stew is thickened, stirring occasionally.
Yields about 8 servings.

title: tennessee chocolate cake
directions: Place sugar and flour in bowl and mix well.
Bring to a rapid boil the shortening, cocoa, margarine and water.
Remove from heat and pour over sugar and flour.
Beat well.
Add vanilla, soda, buttermilk and eggs.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil. Fry until golden brown.

title: chicken salad pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and put into pie crust.
Top with Cheddar cheese and chopped olives, if desired.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Crust:
Add 1 stick margarine (melted) and sugar to crushed graham crackers.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and add to mushrooms.
Cover and stir. Marinate 24 hours in refrigerator.	Makes about 4 cups.

title: economy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
You may add nuts, raisins or chocolate chips if you like.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop dough by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool before serving.
Makes about 48 cookies.

title: aunt eaqu's vinegar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vinegar and mix well.
Add flour and soda; mix.
Add pecans, if desired.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° until lightly browned.
These cookies are delicious and similar to shortbread.

title: sausage cheese strata
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Place 5 bread slices on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with 5 slices cheese, sausage and remaining bread slices.
Combine eggs, milk and green onion and pour over bread.
Cover.
Refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Bake uncovered until cheese topping begins to melt.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop beef into small pieces and set aside. In a bowl, cream remaining ingredients together. Add 2 tablespoons chopped beef to mixture and blend well. Form mixture into a ball and cover with remaining beef. Chill until ready to serve with your favorite crackers.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine
first five ingredients in double boiler.
Stir until thick.
Remove
from
heat.
Add margarine and vanilla. Beat until
smooth
and creamy.	Pour into a baked 9-inch pie shell. Top with meringue.	Chill and serve.

title: pot roast
directions: Place a large sheet of heavy-duty foil in pan without lid. Lay meat on foil after rubbing both sides generously with steak sauce.
Sprinkle dried onion soup mix on top and pour cream of mushroom soup over this.
Close foil over meat loosely.
(It makes its own gravy.)
Crimp foil to hold in heat.
Cook in slow oven (250° to 300°) for 1 hour for each pound of meat. (Can also be cooked in crock-pot, but omit foil.)

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Cool, peel and shred.
Combine grated cheese and butter until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and stir lightly.
Put in casserole.
Dot with butter and bake 25 minutes or until hot.
Bake at 350°.
May be assembled day before.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix ingredients in this order.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes in greased cake pans.
Makes 3 layers.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Better to let stand a few hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° until set in center.

title: beef and beans
directions: Put roast in slow cooker and add everything around it. Cover. Cook at 250° for 10 to 12 hours.

title: spinach fettucini carbonara
directions: Saute Prosciutto ham, onion and garlic in oil about 5 minutes. Add pasta and cream; cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in eggs, salt and pepper, tossing until evenly coated.
Garnish with tomato and serve with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: sour pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Place in jars.
Put a pinch of alum in each jar.
Combine salt, vinegar and water.
Boil until salt dissolves. Pour over pickles.
Use same recipe for dill pickles.
Just add a dill sprig and a pinch of garlic to each jar.
Seal.

title: creamy "no bean" dip
directions: Let cream cheese warm to room temperature and put in microwavable bowl; add beanless chili to cream cheese and heat on High until able to mix together well.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: dump bars
directions: Dump all ingredients except chocolate chips together in a bowl. Mix with spoon until moistened.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Do not stir.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: summertime tea
directions: In a pitcher steep tea bags in boiling water for 5 minutes. Discard tea bags.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl with a spoon.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 1 hour before removing.
The cake could also be baked in three 9-inch layer pans.
If so, bake only 30 minutes.
Cake can be frozen.

title: easy pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions until tender but firm. Rinse with cold water.
Cut vegetables in chunks.
Mix vegetables with pasta and add salad dressing.
Mix in salad seasoning to taste.

title: emerald soup
directions: You will need 4 soup bowls (bread).

Place broccoli flowerets in a 2-quart bowl. Stir in onion. Microwave (covered) for 7 minutes. Let rest for 2 minutes. Add chicken and soups (x 3). Microwave (covered) for 5 minutes. Pour in milk to desired consistency. Microwave (covered) another 5 minutes. Serve in bread bowls.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Generously grease pan.
Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Combine eggs, oil and buttermilk and add to dry ingredients.
Pour into pan and bake for 25 minutes or until done.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut beef into small pieces.
Cut bacon into small pieces; fry in heavy large skillet.
Remove bacon; brown beef in bacon fat. Add garlic, mushrooms, bay leaf, parsley, salt, thyme, pepper and bacon.
In another pan, melt butter.
Add flour; stir constantly until flour turns light tan.
Add consomme and Burgundy wine; stir and cook until slightly thickened.
Add to beef and mushrooms. Cover; simmer for about 2 hours, or until beef is tender.
May be made ahead and reheated in a casserole at 350° until bubbly. Serve over rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fiesta hard rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon mixture into sourdough rolls that have been hollowed in center.
Place in wax sandwich bags and heat in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix the first six ingredients together.
Form balls approximately 3/4-inch in diameter, then roll them in powdered sugar.
Store in a cookie tin or container with tight fitting lid overnight.
Cheers!

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef; add taco seasoning. Simmer for 20 minutes. Drain ground beef. Put chili and cheese in crock pot, stirring frequently. Add seasoned hamburger.

title: ham and cheese muffins
directions: Beat milk, oil and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients with a fork until moistened.
Grease mini muffin pans and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from beef; cut in strips.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add beef; cook until brown, about 5 minutes.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to boiling and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 12 to 15 minutes for round steak and 5 to 8 minutes for sirloin.
Add green pepper strips during the last 5 minutes of simmering.
Cook instant rice.
Blend cornstarch and soy sauce. Stir into beef mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Let boil for 1 minute.
Cut each tomato into eighths and place on beef.
Cover and cook over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: no fuss pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Place in a hallow baking dish (not glass) side by side.
Combine all other ingredients and spoon evenly over chops.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: quick fruit cup
directions: Combine all fruit in a medium bowl; toss gently.
Spoon into individual serving bowl.
Top with a dollop of yogurt.
Garnish with mint, if desired.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in other ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crab dip(or spread)
directions: Drain crab meat, then chop a little to be sure it is shredded finely.
Mix with cream cheese.
Chill about 2 hours; may chill overnight.
Before serving, pour cocktail sauce over top to taste. Great on crackers!

title: strawberry heaven
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Break cake into small pieces. Add to gelatin mixture.
Put into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Chill. Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream on top, plus a fresh strawberry.
Serves 15.

title: toffee
directions: Butter 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread pecans in pan.
Heat sugar and butter to boiling; stir constantly for 7 minutes. Immediately spread mixture evenly over nuts in pan.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces over hot mixture.
Place baking sheet over candy while hot.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Chill until firm.
Makes 3 dozen squares.

title: steak sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until sauce has thickened.
Serve over your favorite steak.

title: german-style potato salad
directions: Cook and peel potatoes.
Cool and slice thinly.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Add remaining ingredients except potatoes and stir.
Cook until sauce thickens (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Pour over potatoes and gently stir. Serve hot.
This may be made ahead of time and warmed in oven or in pot.

title: crisco pie crust
directions: Mix the flour, salt and Crisco until they are mixed well.
(It will form little balls.
May be some flour loose, that's okay but don't leave a lot).
Then add the water.
You may add a little more water if you need it, but not too much at a time.
Roll the dough in your hands until it is a ball.
You know how to do the rest.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add Ragu sauce and parsley flakes.
Simmer.
Boil noodles.
In a bowl, mix 1 well beaten egg. Add cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese; stir.

title: beef and barley mulligan
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large kettle; bring to boil.
Simmer for at least an hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
In large soup pan, add chopped ingredients to browned beef.
Add about 2 quarts water and cook.

title: curried chicken
directions: In a large, heavy kettle, brown/saute sliced onion and mushrooms in oil.
Add cut up chicken.
Add water until the chicken is almost covered.
Add the curry, turmeric powder and black pepper.
Add enough chicken broth mix for the amount of water you added.
Cover and simmer until chicken is cooked.

title: vermont stew
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet with onion, pepper, celery, salt, pepper and chili included.
Then add mashed tomatoes, tomato sauce and English peas; simmer.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Add to beef mixture.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar, corn syrup, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked shell, top with chopped pecans.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: western barbecued beans
directions: Combine beef, salt, pepper and garlic; brown in cooking oil over medium heat.
Add onion and brown a few minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into bean pot or 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: raspberry jello
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Mix chopped cabbage and onions.
Brown in a 300° oven the sesame seed, almonds and noodles.
Let cool.
Mix with cabbage and onions.

title: beef ball
directions: Chop scallions and 1 jar of dried beef into fine pieces.
Mix with hands the cream cheese, scallions, 1 jar dried beef, Worcestershire sauce and Accent salt until all ingredients are evenly mixed.
Roll into a ball.
Finely chop second jar of dried beef.
Roll ball onto beef until completely covered by beef.
Let sit 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve as a spread on crackers.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Mix sugar with rhubarb.
Let set overnight.
Add Jell-O.
Cook until thick.
Pour in sterilized jars and seal.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes.
Mash.
Beat cream cheese and sour cream until well blended. Add hot potatoes gradually until well blended. Add milk if too stiff.
Season to taste.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a greased 2-quart casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream of crab meat soup
directions: Combine soups in saucepan; add milk and cream.
Stir well; heat but not boil.
Add crab meat.
Add sherry just before serving. Place piece of butter in bottom of soup tureen or place pat of butter in bottom of individual bowls.
Pour hot soup over; serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into quiche pan (about 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped green onions and chopped tomato pieces.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: no-crust coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and beat.
Add water, milk, flavoring, butter and flour; mix well, then stir in coconut.
Pour in a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until coconut browns and pie is set.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix well beaten eggs with flour, sugar and 1/2 of milk.
Put rest of milk in pan over hot water.
Pour egg mixture into hot milk, stirring constantly using a whisk.
Strain before it gets cool.
Season with bourbon next day according to your taste. Serve with ice cream or whipping cream.

title: company meatballs
directions: Mix beef, sour cream, onion soup mix, eggs and crumbs; form into small balls and roll in flour and paprika mixture.
Put in baking dish; cover with soup and water mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes approximately 50 small meatballs.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken with the bouillon cubes.
Debone chicken and place in casserole dish.
Mix together the broth and soup; pour over chicken.
Melt margarine in saucepan; pour corn bread stuffing in and stir until mixed well.
Spread stuffing over top of chicken.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut casserole - kalamazoo
directions: Toss ingredients together and put into a casserole dish.
Dot butter on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.
This is much better than you would expect.
It improves when reheated.

title: fiesta guacamole dip
directions: In small bowl combine refried beans and chilies; spread on large serving plate.
Combine sour cream and taco seasoning, spread evenly over top of bean mixture.
In small bowl, mash avocados; stir in lime or lemon juice and salts.
Spoon evenly over sour cream mixture. Cover and chill for several hours.
Just before serving, garnish with cheeses, tomatoes, green onions and olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: creamed spinach
directions: In medium saucepan, over medium heat, saute shallots in butter 3 minutes or until softened.
Blend in flour and nutmeg; saute 2 minutes.
Blend in milk; cook 2 minutes or until very thick, whisking constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in cream cheese.
Add spinach and seasoning; mix well.
Heat until hot.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream.
Makes 6 servings.
Per serving 173 calories, 7 g protein, 13 g carbohydrate, 12 g fat, 33 mg cholesterol and 447 mg sodium.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Cut out center of rye bread and make cubes out of it.
Mix and chill the sour cream, mayonnaise, parsley, onion and beef.
When ready to serve, fill the rye bread with preceding mixture.
Place cubes of bread along the side.
Use the cubes to dip.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar, lemon juice and gelatin (mixed in water). Bring to boil; put in refrigerator to congeal.
Grate cheese and add to mixture with Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Garnish with grated cheese and cherries.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add melted oleo, juice and vanilla.
Add coconut last.
Add 1 cup chocolate chips for variety. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit delight
directions: Melt
butter
and
brown sugar.
Mix buttermilk, yogurt and fruit.
Put
yogurt
mixture
in bottom of casserole dish. Pour butter/sugar
mixture over.
Sprinkle coconut and cereal over top. Bake at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut thin
slice from the top of each tomato.
Scoop out pulp and set aside. Drain tomatoes upside down.	Cook bacon in a 12-inch
Dutch oven.
Drain off grease.
Add bell pepper and onion.
Saute
until
soft.
Remove
from heat.
Blend cheese, lettuce and tomato	pulp.
Fill
each tomato shell with 1/4 of the mixture.
Sprinkle
with saltine crumbs and 1 teaspoon of margarine
(melted) each.
Place in 8-inch Dutch oven. Bake 30 minutes with 12 coals on top and 10 coals on the bottom.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add eggs, vinegar and coconut. Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: caponata
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Saute eggplant, mushrooms, onion, garlic, basil, oregano and pepper for 10 minutes.
Blend in tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes.
Stir in vinegar.
Serve warm or cold with sliced bread or crackers.

title: carrot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until thick; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into dish or lightly greased mold. Chill until firm.
Recipe from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Saute onion in 6 tablespoons butter until golden.
Cut squash into cubes and add to onion.
Stir in cheese, Accent, salt and pepper.
Cool slightly.
Mix vegetables lightly with beaten eggs; spoon into shallow buttered baking dish.
Toss remaining 2 tablespoons of melted butter with bread crumbs and sprinkle over top of zucchini mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan meringues
directions: Beat egg white until frothy; add salt.
Add sugars to beaten egg white; blend well.
Add nuts and stir lightly to coat.
Lift halves individually with fork and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 200° on upper shelf of oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn and switch pan to lower shelf and bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Because ovens cook differently, watch carefully to avoid burning.
Let cool in oven with door propped open.
Remove from pan with spatula.
Enjoy these crunchy delights.

title: jim's buttermilk cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, creaming after each addition.
Add sifted flour to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk and soda.
Pour in large angel food cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: triscuits cheddar and broccoli
directions: Arrange wafers on a large microwavable plate.
Top with broccoli and cheese.
Microwave at High (100%) power for 1 minute; rotate plate 1/4 turn.
Cook for 10 to 20 seconds more or until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: crabmeat rangoons
directions: Chop crab and onions.
Mix with cream cheese and garlic.
Put a teaspoonful or two on wonton wrap; fold up burrito style.
Deep fry until golden.

title: farmers breakfast
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove to paper towel to drain.
In drippings, saute onion and potatoes until potatoes are browned, about 5 minutes.
Pour eggs into skillet; cook and stir gently until eggs are set and cooked to desired doneness. Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon; let stand for 2-3 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: "spice of life" (salt substitute)
directions: Place all the ingredients in a small electric coffee grinder, spice grinder or blender. Grind for 10 seconds or until the mixture is fine.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: (Chill beaters before whipping cream.)
In a large mixing bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 or 6 minutes.

Fold in whipped cream. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into a 2 1/2-quart round glass bowl. Top with 1/3 each of the wafers, bananas and pudding mixture. Repeat this layering twice, ending with pudding mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Top with Cool Whip or whipping cream and wafers around the edges.
No cooking necessary with this light, fluffy dessert.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish with nonstick spray.
Evenly distribute the rice on the bottom of the dish.
Layer the pork chops, then bell pepper rings, onion rings and tomatoes (with liquid).
Add Worcestershire sauce evenly over top to taste. Add enough water to cover rice and partially cover pork chops. Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until rice and veggies are done.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, then chocolate and butter melted together.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a 9-inch pan for 20 minutes or until done.

title: buttered fruit
directions: Drain fruit and place in a casserole dish.
Add 1 stick butter to this.
Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup brown sugar.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: slushy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except water together.
Add water to make a gallon.
Place in freezer and shake several times to make slush.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together well with pastry blender.
Spread into a 10 x 15-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Add onion soup and Cheez Whiz (Cheddar cheese, optional).
Saute celery in oleo.
Pour boiling water over broccoli and drain.
Combine all together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Add Cheddar to top.
Serve hot.

title: ultimate turtle cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Press into bottom 2-inches upside of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Microwave caramels and milk on High 3 minutes or until caramels completely melt.
Stir every minute. Pour 1/2 mixture over crumb crust.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Set remaining mixture aside.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla on medium until blended.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing on low until blended.
Pour over caramel mixture in crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool before removing sides of pan. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Top with remaining caramel mixture and pecans before serving.
Melt chocolate as directed on packaging; drizzle over cheesecake.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add tomato juice to meat in large 5 or 6-quart soup pan.
Add onion, carrots, potatoes and green beans.
Cook over medium to medium-high heat (slow boil) for 35 to 45 minutes.
Add corn, boiling for 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Turn burner off and allow to cool for 10 minutes.
Serve with crackers or peanut butter sandwiches.

title: cinnamon-sugared doughnut drops
directions: In large saucepan, heat 2 to 3 inches of oil to 375°.
In large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in milk, oil, vanilla and egg with fork just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop by teaspoons into hot oil 5 or 6 at a time.
Fry doughnut drops 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Roll warm doughnut balls in sugar-cinnamon mixture, makes about 30 to 36 doughnut balls.

title: chocolate cherry cordial muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, 1 3/4 cups morsels, brown sugar, granulated sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in cherries.
In small bowl combine milk, oil and egg until well blended.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened.
Spoon batter into 12 greased or paper-lined muffin cups.
Muffin cups will be full.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup morsels.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan; serve warm or cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Wrap bacon around tenderloins and secure with toothpicks; place in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over tenderloins.
Place in refrigerator and let stand for 4 or 5 hours, turning often.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until internal temperature reaches 170°, basting often.
Turn meat once. Serves 12.

title: uncooked fondant
directions: Mix until creamy.
Tint as desired with few drops of food coloring.
Drop small spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Decorate with nuts, candied fruits or silver dragees.
Let stand to become firm.

title: janice graham's cornbread
directions: Heat milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and oil.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Measure dry ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Add warm milk mixture and yeast.
Stir until well blended, then knead about 2 minutes in bowl.
Form into 2 loaves and place in medium size greased loaf pans.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes delicious toast for breakfast.
Freezes nicely.

title: s'mores bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine in a large bowl at medium speed until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
In a small bowl, combine flour and graham cracker crumbs.
Add to margarine mixture; mix well.
Press in bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with marshmallows, chocolate morsels and pecans.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool; cut into bars.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Yield: 2 to 3 servings.

title: plum butter
directions: Wash and cook plums in a little water until tender.
Press through a strainer.
Add sugar and spices to pulp; cook over low heat for about 45 minutes or until mixture thickens; stir often. Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Yields 4 pints.

title: yellow dream cake
directions: Layer cake can use loaf pan.

title: crockpot potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients in crockpot.
Cook on high for 6 hours or on low all day.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: To 1 teaspoon oil, add carrots and broccoli.
Add garlic salt to taste; stir-fry for about 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
To 1 teaspoon oil, add chicken; stir-fry for 5 minutes, or until chicken is white.
Add soy sauce, sherry and sugar; simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove chicken, but leave drippings.
Add chicken broth; bring to a boil.
Add rice; cook until done (20 minutes).
Add all ingredients; simmer for 5 minutes.

title: chili cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salted water for 8 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Mix mayonnaise, chili sauce and dill seed; fold into cabbage.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.
Your time: 7 minutes.
Cooking time: 8 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookie
directions: Cut fruit and nuts into large pieces.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream butter and add sugar gradually beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Beat eggs into creamed mixture; add fruit and nuts.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 150 cookies.

title: turkey stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet or wok, stir-fry turkey in oil until no longer pink, 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir-fry the onion, carrot, green pepper and mushrooms until crisp-tender.
In a small bowl, combine chicken broth, soy sauce, cornstarch and ginger.
Add to the skillet; cook and stir until thick.
Return meat to skillet with pea pods; cook and stir until heated through.
Serve over rice. Chicken can be substituted for turkey.

title: joyce's broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and put into greased casserole dish.
Mix soup, eggs, dressing, cheese and onions.
Pour over broccoli.
In small bowl, stir croutons in butter, then sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; then add eggs and corn.
Next, add vegetables, milk and oil.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a greased pan.
Top with 1/2 of the cheese.
Pour remaining batter into pan and top with rest of cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cover dressed hen with cold water and let boil gently until tender.
There should be about 2 cups broth left when chicken is cooked.
When cool, remove meat from bones and cut in not too small pieces; add to the 2 cups broth.
Boil 2 cups rich milk; add to the chicken, then season with salt, red pepper and black pepper.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender in water; drain and mash.
Brown onion in oil; add to squash.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add cheese chips, salt and pepper to taste; mix well.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fiesta tamale pie
directions: Brown beef in skillet until crumbly.
Mix in onion, green pepper, salt, chili seasoning mix and tomatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in corn and olives.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine corn meal, salt and water in a saucepan.
Cook, stirring until thick.
Spread evenly over beef mixture, or make a 2-inch border of the corn meal mixture around the edge of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake until cheese is browned and melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill overnight.
Serve with chips.

title: festive spoon cake
directions: Cut fruit into small pieces.
Combine with water, 3/4 cup sugar, lemon juice and allspice in a medium skillet.
Boil 10 minutes (medium heat).
Cover and set aside.
Stir together, by hand, 1/2 cup sugar and margarine.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon.
Reserve drippings in skillet.
Crumble and set aside.
Cook onion in drippings until tender.
Stir in beans and remaining ingredients.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Top with bacon.
Let stand before serving.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Prepare apples.
In a saucepan put juice, cinnamon and cornstarch, cook stirring constantly till thickened.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins.
Put in pie shell and dot with butter. Arrange top crust.	Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: green beans caesar
directions: Combine beans, onion, garlic, oil and vinegar.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish. Combine crumbs, cheese and margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dreamy creamy fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease Bundt pan.
In small bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, cream and melted chocolate; beat until smooth.

title: mint pie
directions: Mix cookies and hot water. Spoon into crust and gently spread to cover bottom. Beat cream cheese until smooth, gradually beat in sugar, milk and peppermint. Fold in cool whip. Stir in food coloring. Fill pie crust. Chill for 3 hours. Decorate with candies, holly leaves with berries.
tags: Graham Cracker ready crust Pie Crust

title: cajun catfish cubes
directions: Mix flour cornmeal and all spices in a large bowl.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Dip catfish cubes into eggs and then into flour mix.
Deep fry until cubes float.

title: hot ham, chicken or turkey salad
directions: Mix all together and put into a greased
9x9 inch baking dish. Sprinkle with crushed corn flakes. Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes. Makes 6-8 servings.

title: whipped turnip puff
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Turn into greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 C. boiling water.
Stir in berries and salt.
Fold in whipping cream.
Tear angel food cake into small pieces and put in 13 x 9 pan.
Pour jello and whipped cream mixture over cake and refrigerate until set (several hours).
Serves:

title: wisconsin dairyland slices
directions: Melt 1 cup butter, sugar and cocoa over hot water. Remove from heat. Add 2 eggs, beaten with a fork. Mix. Pour over cracker crumbs and coconut. Mix and press into large 12 x 18 pan (or cookie pan). Freeze.

title: mandel brot
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Put in sugar, eggs, oil and extract.
Add almonds.
Knead together.
Divide into 3 or 4 loaves.
Use 1 cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Cut diagonally. Put back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: granny's cornbread
directions: Melt shortening in iron frying pan (bigger one) and get pan really hot.
In a bowl, mix cornmeal, sugar, egg and buttermilk and mix well.
Then pour hot grease in mixture.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: stewed tomato dip(8 to 9 pint jars)
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a fast boil.
Simmer 40 to 50 minutes, stirring frequently, to prevent sticking.
Refrigerate!!

title: bread pudding with whiskey sauce* * * * *
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, beating with a wire whisk.
Add bread and raisins; stir well.
Spoon mixture into 8 (6 ounce) custard cups coated with spray.
Place cups in a large shallow pan; add hot water, to a depth of 3/4-inch, to pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Spoon Whiskey Sauce over pudding.

title: almond oriental chicken salad
directions: Combine teriyaki sauce, lemon juice and red pepper flakes. Beat in oil.
Toss with almonds and remaining ingredients. Serves 4 to 6.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder and salt, alternating with milk.
Add flavorings and coconut.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 45 minutes more or until done.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Combine graham crackers, oleo and sugar.
Press in pan.
Beat cream cheese and 10x sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over graham crust.
Spread pie filling over top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies(oatmeal orange-raisin) *
directions: Put shortening, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla in bowl and mix well.
Sift together and add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add oatmeal, chocolate chips* and raisins. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on lightly greased pan; bake in 350° oven for approximately 10 minutes.
Cool 1 to 2 minutes on pan before removing to rack.
Makes 6 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: our pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese.
Add pineapple, pepper, onion, salt and 1 cup nuts.
Roll into ball.
Use remaining 1 cup nuts to roll cheese ball in.

title: luncheon jello
directions: Combine the ingredients; refrigerate until firm.

title: honey chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Remove skin from chicken, if desired.
Dip each piece of chicken in sauce and place in a large greased roasting pan.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: nevelle's cheese straws
directions: Cream cheese and butter.
Add flour and Rice Krispies.
Mix until well blended.
Form into small balls about the size of walnuts.
Place on cookie sheet lightly greased or sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix margarine, oil, sugar, vanilla and egg in large bowl until it turns to cream.
Then add rest of ingredients, stir well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Grease bottom of pan.
Dip in sugar, flatten thin.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
