directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Blend all ingredients on low speed, using hand mixer for 1 minute.
Beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pans and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes and then remove from pans.

title: coke roast
directions: Rub roast with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Brown roast on all sides in oil.
Remove and pat dry with paper towel to remove all fat.
Place roast in foil lined pan and pour Coke over.
Pour chili sauce over roast and then Worcestershire sauce.
You can also use Tabasco sauce to taste.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake for 3 hours at 325°.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and let stand until cool. Stir the beaten egg into the Grape-Nut mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 4.

title: my mom's eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in salted water until just tender.
Drain.
Add soup, eggs, sugar, onion and cheese.
Add 1/2 cup of the crumbs. Put in a casserole dish.
Pour melted oleo over top and sprinkle with other 1/2 cup crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into four pieces each.
Coat each piece in sugar mixture and place together in a Bundt cake pan.
After all pieces are coated and in pan, melt butter and pour over remaining sugar mixture.
Mix together and pour over coated biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and turn pan upside-down onto plate. Pull apart to serve.

title: catfish stew
directions: Put fish in pot with 1 cup water; add potatoes, onions, butter and 2 tablespoons flour with 1/2 cup cold water.
Cook 30 minutes. Add milk and cream.
Stir.
Turn off heat.
Serve hot with crackers or corn bread.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in loaf pan.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Store in an airtight container.

title: the best salad
directions: Freeze Gorgonzola cheese.
Rinse lettuce; set aside to thoroughly dry.
Mince garlic and place it with olive oil in a container with a tight fitting lid.
Shake oil and garlic vigorously and chill.
Chop lettuce for salad and chill in large salad bowl.
Finely crumble the frozen Gorgonzola cheese into small container and return to freezer.
Pour oil and garlic mixture over lettuce; toss well.
Sprinkle vinegar, salt and Accent over lettuce; toss well.
Sprinkle half of Gorgonzola cheese over lettuce; toss.
Top remaining Gorgonzola cheese over salad.
Garnish with black olives.
Chill and serve on chilled plates.

title: prune spice cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; blend in prunes.
Combine all dry ingredients and spices, add to mixture.
Beat buttermilk into batter; add pecans.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water.
Cool slightly; peel and thinly slice.
Add onions and next 3 ingredients.
Mix and keep warm. Cook bacon crisp and drain, reserving drippings.
Mix vinegar, sugar and water with cool bacon drippings.
Heat to simmering. Add very slowly to beaten egg, beating constantly.
Pour over potatoes.
Add crumbled bacon and parsley.
Mix lightly and serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Roll into balls and dip into sugar.
Then bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-lima bean casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and lima beans until almost tender.
Mix soup, sour cream and onion soup together.
Add in broccoli, lima beans and sliced water chestnuts.
Put in buttered casserole.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together eggs, margarine and sugar.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix bananas and nuts into mixture.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and set aside.

title: amaretto slush
directions: Combine sugar and water, bring to boil - stirring until sugar dissolves, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: surprise cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix according to box.
Fill cupcake pans 2/3 full with cake batter.
Drop rounded teaspoonful of mixture into the middle of each cupcake.
Bake according to box.
Let cool, then frost.

title: yeast bread
directions: Scald milk; add shortening, salt and sugar.
While cooling, dissolve yeast cakes in lukewarm water.
When cool, add to milk and shortening mixture.
Use flour to make a stiff dough (try 5 to 6 cups).
Let rise 2 hours.
Shape into rolls or loaves.
Rise 1 hour and bake at 425°.

title: chicken in tomato-wine sauce(this recipe is heart healthy)
directions: Place all ingredients, except mushrooms and wine, in a large pot.
Cover and simmer 1 hour over flames so low that liquid barely quivers on top.
Add mushrooms and wine and cook for 5 minutes more.
Serve garnished with parsley.
Yields 4 servings. Approximate cal/serving:

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan, melt the butter. Set aside to cool.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs with an electric mixer.
Add the sugars and flour, continuing to beat until the mix is light and creamy.
Beat in the cooled butter until thoroughly incorporated.
Stir in the chocolate chips and walnuts with a mixing spoon.
Pour the filling into the pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in large iron skillet.

title: venison jerky
directions: Slice venison not more than 1/4-inch thick or thinner.
Mix ingredients together; add enough water to cover meat.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Lay on oven rack.
Bake at 150° with oven slightly ajar until meat is dry.
Cool completely before storing. Store in airtight container.
Will keep 1 year.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine flour, oatmeal, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix all ingredients.
Add chocolate chips, chopped nuts and grated Hershey bar.
Place golf ball size cookies 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Makes approximately 112 cookies.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Ball, then bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Cook hamburger meat with bell peppers and onion until done while cooking macaroni according to package directions.
Drain both.
Add macaroni to beef mixture.
Add stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes on low.
Add salt or garlic salt and pepper as desired.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Cool.
Add rest of the ingredients and let set in refrigerator until Jell-O gets firm. Serve on lettuce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Make stuffing mix and place in a greased casserole dish. Mix chicken, soup, onions and enough milk to make it a nice consistency. Pour over stuffing. Put bread crumbs or crackers on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: curried chicken-vegetable stew
directions: Combine breast halves, onion, garlic, red pepper and water in large Dutch oven.
Bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes or until tender.
Remove breast halves from broth. Skim fat from broth.
Bone chicken.
Cut into bite-size pieces. Combine broth, chicken, chopped vegetables and remaining ingredients in pan.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer 30 minutes. Yield:
9 cups.

title: surprise party dip
directions: Mix together until thoroughly blended.
Chill until served. May be served with chips or raw veggies.

title: smoked salmon ball
directions: Mix together and chill for 1 hour, then roll into shape of ball and roll in nuts. Dry in parsley flakes.

title: lone star caviar dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: egg casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch casserole dish; line with 3 to 4 pieces of bread.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Add cheese to mixture, then crumble in the meat.
Pour over bread and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for approximately 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Should resemble a custard in consistency. When done, cut into squares and serve.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add juice from cocktail.
Add flour and beat well. Add fruit.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle top of batter with brown sugar and nuts.
Cook at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: almond tea
directions: Steep tea bags in 2 cups boiling water for 10 minutes.
Boil sugar in 4 cups water for 5 minutes and then add lemon juice and flavorings. Combine the liquids and heat. Serve hot or cold.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs and melted butter, flour and sugar.
Beat and fold in coconut; add milk.
Pour in ungreased pan or loaf pan.
Bake 40 minutes to an hour at 350°.
Makes its own crust.

title: fried okra
directions: Cook okra until tender in a small amount of water.
Drain. Combine remaining ingredients, except oil.
Mix lightly.
Place oil in a large skillet, add okra mixture and fry over medium high heat, stirring often.
Fry until golden brown, approximately 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: apple fritters
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, nutmeg and cinnamon.
In a large measuring cup or small bowl, combine oil, egg and milk.
Beat with a wire whisk to blend.
Add to dry ingredients and stir.
Fold in chopped apples.
Drop batter by tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle the tops with powdered sugar.
Serve warm or cold.

title: thimble cookies(rich, short cookies topped with jam!!)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour.
If necessary, chill until firm enough to handle.
With floured hands, roll into 1-inch balls. Place 1 1/2-inches apart on cookie sheets.
Using a floured thimble, make a small indentation in center of each cookie.
Fill with jam.
Bake at 325° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on racks. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: old-time bread pudding
directions: Cube bread and place in a 2-quart greased baking dish. Sprinkle with raisins.
Mix eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, salt, milk and water and pour over bread and raisins.
Let set for 10 minutes. Add vanilla and stir.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no-cook fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients with an electric mixer.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator for 20 minutes; cut.

title: sizzling cheese sandwiches
directions: Dice bacon and brown.
Drain and place on paper towel to cool. Shred cheese and place in large bowl.
Dice black olives.
Mix all ingredients and spread on party rye.
Broil until golden brown.

title: peach pie
directions: Cook 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Put in baked pie shell.
Serve with Cool Whip topping.

title: tamale pie
directions: In a large skillet brown ground beef, stirring to break up pieces.
Add
celery, pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook until vegetables are
tender.
Add
tomato
sauce
and chili powder. Heat
thoroughly,
stirring
occasionally.	Spoon into 2-quart casserole dish.
Prepare cornbread mix using the egg and milk. Pour on top
of chili mixture.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until bread is brown.
Serves 6.

title: monkey bread
directions: Stir together white sugar and 4 tablespoons cinnamon.
Cut each biscuit in half; dip in cinnamon mixture.
Place in greased tube pan.

title: betty jean's boiled custard
directions: Stir sugar and flour together and just a little milk.
Add egg yolks, then add the rest of the milk.
Add some vanilla and nutmeg.
Start by cooking 1 minute on high, stirring after every minute.
When it gets hot, you can cook for 2 minutes.

title: delicious candy
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Add softened butter and nuts.
Mix well and add coconut.
Roll into 1/2-inch balls and refrigerate until chilled.
Melt 3/4 bar paraffin and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Keep hot and dip chilled candy into chocolate mixture. Put on waxed paper to cool and harden.
Store in a cool place.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Combine oregano, salt and pepper; sprinkle on chicken.
Brown in oil in a 6-quart Dutch oven; remove.
Cut green pepper into strips.
Add with onions, garlic, bay leaf and red pepper to drippings; saute for 5 minutes.
Add rice and cook, stirring, until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes and chicken broth.
Arrange chicken on top.
Bake (tightly covered) in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Remove; do not stir.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Arrange peas, olives and peppers on top.
Bake, covered, 20 minutes longer.

title: baked scallops
directions: Use your favorite fish fillet.
Crush some Ritz crackers in a plastic bag.
Put a few slabs of butter in a pyrex dish.
Sprinkle half the crushed crackers on top of butter.
Place fish on top of butter.
Place crushed crackers on top of fillets.
Put some butter on top of crackers.
Bake or broil until done.
If needed, add more butter.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Prepare 1 package chocolate pudding mix (cooked type).
Blend dry devil's food cake mix into hot pudding.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan, 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inches.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chocolate pieces and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake in 350° (moderate) oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken and gravy in oven with potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Salt and pepper the chicken pieces. Put flour in a bag.
Shake the chicken pieces in it.
Do not shake off excess flour.
Arrange chicken in a single layer in a roasting pan (I use a medium size enamel roaster).
Sprinkle more of the flour (about 1/4 cup) over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes or until flour is starting to brown.
Add 2 to 3 cups of boiling water and arrange the potatoes, onion and garlic over chicken. Cover and continue baking at 450° until chicken and potatoes are done, about another hour.
Check after about 30 minutes.
If gravy is too thick, add a little water.

title: baked pork chops with apples
directions: Sprinkle each pork chop with salt and paprika.
Brown in lightly greased frying pan.
Place pork chops in baking dish.
Put apples, skin side down, on chops.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Pour cream in bottom of pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until apples are tender.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix together the following ingredients until well blended: drained clams, sour cream, parsley, onion salt, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Place in a serving bowl, sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter oatmeal muffins
directions: Add oats and milk; mix until blended.
Let set for 30 minutes. Mix together flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl; set aside. Cream together the peanut butter, margarine, brown sugar and egg. Add oats and milk mixture until blended.
Add flour mixture and mix only until flour is moistened.
Do not overmix.
Stir in raisins or chocolate chips just until mixed.
Spoon batter into greased (or lined) muffin pans.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: punch
directions: Slowly add cranberry juice to sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add pineapple juice.
Chill.
Then add ginger ale. Makes 32 cups.

title: lady's day-out casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Brown meat and onions.
Add salt, pepper, spaghetti sauce and tomatoes.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Place 1/2 of the macaroni in 2 1/2-quart casserole. Cover with half of the meat mixture, then half of the cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix drained fruits, add jello and applesauce. Fold in cool whip. Chill and serve.

title: quick caramel coffee ring
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, melt margarine.
Coat bottom and sides of 12-cup tube pan with 2 tablespoons of the melted margarine.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of the nuts over the bottom of prepared pan.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Cook together beef and onion.
Spread in a casserole dish. Top with vegetables, cream of chicken soup and then top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugars and salt, then add beaten eggs and cream; blending well.
Add melted butter and mix thoroughly.
Cover bottom of pan with pecans.
Pour in other mixture and bake in oven, about 30 minutes or until preset.
Pie is done when all but a small circle in the middle is set.
This part will cook after removing from the oven by heat from the pie.

title: sugar cured ham
directions: Pick beans when they are full of bean.
Dry them either by stringing on a string and hanging them up or break them and spread them out on newspaper or old sheets in the sun.

title: biscuits
directions: *I always use the sugar.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Butter casserole; layer broccoli, cauliflower and egg slices. Sprinkle cheese over eggs and put the soup on top.
Sprinkle crumbs (buttered) on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soup and sour cream.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine crackers and margarine.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: creamy mushroom soup
directions: Heat oil in heavy large Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add shallots and garlic and saut until translucent, about 3 minutes.
Add all mushrooms; saut until mushrooms wilt and liquid evaporates, about 7 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour.
Stir 2 minutes.
Gradually mix in stock.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix in 1 cup cream.
Simmer until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Season to taste with nutmeg, salt and pepper. (Can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate. Bring to simmer before serving, thinning with more cream if desired.)
Stir parsley into soup.
Ladle into bowls and serve. Makes 6 servings.

title: caramel brownies
directions: In heavy pan, melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Set aside. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, margarine, 1/3 cup milk and nuts.
Stir until dough holds together.
Press 1/2 of dough in pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked crust.
Spread caramel mixture over chips.
Crumble remaining mixture on top.
Bake for 16 to 18 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: squash stuffing casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the squash and onion in boiling salted water for 5 to 10 minutes or until crisp and tender.
Drain well.
In a large bowl, combine soup and sour cream (or milk). Stir in carrots and fold in squash and onion.
Toss stuffing mix with melted butter. Spread half the stuffing mix in a 7 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spoon squash mixture on top.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: picante chicken with peppers
directions: You will need 1 Reynolds oven cooking bag (large size).

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream softened margarine and cream cheese; add egg and flavoring.
Beat well.
Add dry
cake mix, then add chopped pecans.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 minutes or until browned.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice in casserole;
cover with onion soup mix. Place chicken
breasts on top.
Mix remaining soups with water and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour in cherry pie filling (do not stir).
Pour in pineapple (do not stir).
Pour in dry cake mix (do not stir). Place pecans over the top.
Cut margarine into pats and place over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wonder buns
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over frozen rolls. Let stand overnight in cool room.
Do not cover. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and slice squash.
Place sliced squash in a casserole dish.
Cover squash with the soup and onion. Next, sprinkle all of cheese.
Finally, sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Bake for 45 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: easy pumpkin-nut pie
directions: Prepare Nut Cookie Crust.
Heat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs slightly in large bowl; stir in pumpkin, brown sugar, cinnamon, salt, cloves, ginger and nutmeg until smooth; gradually stir in evaporated milk.
Pour into crust.
Cover edge with 2 to 3-inch strips of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake until knife inserted near center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes longer; cool pie completely.
Prepare Brown Sugar Whipped Cream.
Serve pie with Brown Sugar Whipped Cream.
Cover and refrigerate any remaining pie and whipped cream.

title: pigs in the blanket
directions: Open the biscuits, putting 2 biscuits together to make patties.
Place a wiener on each patty and wrap around, pinching to secure connection.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until dough is light brown.

title: peanut butter parfait
directions: Mix Oreo crumbs and melted oleo.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, saving 1 cup for top.
Spoon softened ice cream over cookies. Pour fudge ice cream topping over top, then sprinkle with Spanish peanuts.
Cover the top with Cool Whip; sprinkle reserved cup of cookie crumbs on top.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put uncooked rice in casserole dish.
Brown pork chops and place on top of rice.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients until the meat is brown.
Drain fat.
Combine remaining ingredients except noodles and stir into meat mixture.
Cook over low heat approximately 20 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: old fashion raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins with water to cover until plump and let stand until cool. Drain and save the juice. Cream together the butter, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy. Sift together all the dry ingredients. Beat all the dry ingredients along with the juice from the raisins and add enough water to make 1 cup. Beat with cream mixture until smooth. Fold in raisins and nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Frost with peanut butter frosting or frosting of your choice.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a saucepan, add sugar and cocoa.
Mix well.
Add milk and margarine.
Cook over medium heat until it comes to a full boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and beat in peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper and cool.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into strips 1/4 inch wide and 1 inch long.
Brown meat in oil.
Push meat to one side and add mushrooms and onion. Saute until onion is soft.
Mix into meat mixture.
Stir in tomato paste (or tomatoes).
Sprinkle flour over all and blend well.
Add sherry or wine and stir until a gravy is formed.
Season to taste. Cover and simmer until meat is tender (about 45 minutes).
Add sour cream just before serving.
Heat through but do not boil. Serve over egg noodles.
Serves 4 hungry people unless you have another side dish, then it could stretch to feed 6.

title: old fashioned lemon cream scones
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
In a medium bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking powder, lemon zest and salt.
Cut in the butter with a fork or a heavy-duty electric mixer until the mixture resembles coarse bread crumbs.
In a small bowl or 1-cup measure, whisk together the eggs and cream.
Add to the dry mixture and stir until a sticky dough is formed.

title: helen's yellow cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients as directed on cake mix for 2 minutes. Add remaining ingredients to mixture.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. (Test with toothpick; when inserted and comes out clean, it's done.)

title: beef and beer stew
directions: Brown stew meat in butter; add salt and pepper to taste.
Saute onions in same pan after meat is removed.
Add teaspoon vinegar and brown sugar.
Layer beef and onions in casserole dish.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups beer.
Top with bay leaves and Grey Poupon mustard. Bake 3 to 4 hours at 350°.

title: cheese porcupine
directions: Combine in a large bowl the first 5 ingredients.
Chop together capers and caraway seed.
Add all together.
Beat until well blended.
Chill.

title: pancho's frozen margaritas
directions: Pour all ingredients in blender.
Fill blender with ice. Blend well.
Pour in glass and serve.

title: filled cookies
directions: Cream shortening and add white sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add brown sugar and beat until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time, then vanilla.
Dissolve soda in sour milk and add to mixture.
Then add salt, baking powder and flour.
Mix well.
Roll out dough and cut circles.
Place 1 tablespoon filling in center and place another circle on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: caribbean fudge pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugar in large bowl until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add chocolate, coffee and rum extract and mix well.
Stir in flour and chopped walnuts.

title: sweet fruit dip
directions: Combine and blend until smooth.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with fruit pieces.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Combine biscuit mix, crumbled sausage and cheese; mix well. Roll into balls about the size of a walnut.
Flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet or freeze and bake when needed.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix together cream of mushroom soup, mayonnaise, Milnot and lemon.
Layer:
Broccoli, chicken, soup mixture and Cheddar cheese.
Top with canned onion rings.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese sauce
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, combine soup and milk.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring often.
Serve over hot cooked vegetables, French fries or omelets.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture boils; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from
heat; add butter and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Serve at room temperature.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix beef, applesauce, eggs, bread, salt and pepper.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in flour.
Brown in hot fat.
Put in casserole.
To drippings in pan, add vegetables and tomato juice. Bring to a boil and pour over meat balls.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: reba's uncooked relish
directions: Grind or chop all veggies and place in glass container or crock.
Add salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain well then squeeze very dry, using hands.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Combine oil, eggs, vanilla, sugar and zucchini and blend. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Do not beat!
Bake in greased muffin pans at 325° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad(low-fat!)
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the chicken, celery, sweet pepper, carrot and onion.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Combine everything in a casserole; top with bread cubes and bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all together and put in pie shell. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix chicken, pasta sauce and vegetables. Pour into greased square pan. Mix Bisquick, Parmesan cheese and butter with fork or pastry blender until crumbly. Stir in egg. Sprinkle over chicken mixture. Bake, uncovered, 20 to 22 minutes or until topping is light golden brown. Serves 6.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice according to usual directions; set aside. Cook broccoli according to pkg. directions and drain. Saute onion in margarine. Combine all ingredients and spoon into a casserole dish. Garnish the top with extra cheese if desired. Bake uncovered for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bone out chicken.
Cook in water to cover until tender.
Remove chicken and save stock.
Add onion and frozen Veg-All to stock. Bring to rolling boil for 5 minutes.
Place shredded boned out chicken in 9 x 13 casserole that has been greased with margarine. Put vegetables on top of chicken.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all but oleo and bread crumbs well.
Pour into baking dish.
Melt oleo and pour over corn mixture.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: orange blossom punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil 5 minutes without stirring; chill. Add juices, ginger ale and pour over ice.

title: butter baked taters
directions: Peel potatoes; cut lengthwise in 3/8-inch slices.
Melt oleo; add salt and garlic salt.
Pour half in jelly roll pan.
Arrange potatoes 1 layer deep in pan.
Spoon on rest of oleo.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes until tender.
If you want them crisp, uncover last 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into ball and cover with crushed cinnamon graham crackers.
Chill.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix chilled milk with other ingredients and pour in a one-quart ice cream freezer.
Fill freezer with alternating layers of crushed ice and rock salt.
Churn until cream is hard.

title: pound cake
directions: Put together in order. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Bake in tube pan.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Lightly grease 12 muffin cups; set aside.
Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg; set aside.
In mixing bowl, cream together 1/2 cup sugar, shortening and egg.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to the creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Fill prepared muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Remove from oven.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: ham delights
directions: Blend first
five
ingredients
together.
Split
rolls lengthwise and spread
top
and
bottom
with blended mixture. Add ham and top with Swiss cheese.
Place rolls back together. Wrap in aluminum foil and heat for 10 minutes in oven, or wrap in plastic wrap and microwave
for
minutes.
Cut into small servings.

title: station ones 4 alarm fire house chili
directions: In Dutch oven, cook crumbled sausage, onion and garlic in hot oil until sausage is no longer pink, drain.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Cut beef in small pieces and put in roasting pan.
Add onion (diced small), peppers (cut in pieces) and potatoes (cut in chunks).
Pour tomato sauce over top of this.
Cover and bake at 350° until all ingredients are done.

title: warm apple crisp
directions: Mix together apples, 1/3 cup sugar, cinnamon, salt and melted butter.
Place in a greased 8-inch square baking dish; set aside. Combine 3/4 cup sugar and flour; cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm with whipped topping.
Makes 8 servings.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add all
other ingredients and mix well.
Spoon mixture into a 3-quart casserole dish and bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Remove seed from peppers and boil 2 minutes in clear water. Drain and cool.
Saute ground beef.
Add onion and can of tomatoes. Cook about 15 minutes on medium.
Add remaining ingredients, but only 1/2 of the tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil and simmer about 30 minutes.
Fill peppers and place in a baking dish.
Pour remaining half of tomato sauce over tops and sprinkle with a little grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian fruit pie
directions: Mix first five ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust. Chill.

title: barbecue pork loin
directions: Boil pork loin 1 hour or until tender.
Mix other ingredients together in a pot over medium heat.
Heat, but do not boil.
Place pork in a baking dish; pour sauce over pork and cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Cream sugar and margarine, and then add mashed bananas, eggs, and pecans.
Sift together the flour and soda.
Then slowly add flour mixture to creamed mixture, stirring well.
Bake for 40 - 55 minutes at 350° in bundt cake pan sprayed well with Pam.
If desired, can be baked as 12 large muffins or 24 miniature muffins. Large muffins take about 25 min. and the smaller size about 15 min.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with oleo over low heat.
Mix together sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add eggs, beating well.
Mix in chocolate mixture.
Add milk and vanilla, beating well.
Pour into pie shells.
Mix coconut and pecans; sprinkle evenly over pies.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
(Check pies after 20 minutes; cover loosely with foil if tops are browning too quickly.)

title: spinach stuffed onions
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat together cream cheese and egg until light; add crumbs, cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in spinach.
Peel onion and cut in half crosswise.
Separate layers and form shells (fill base with smaller onion pieces). Place in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spoon spinach mixture into onion shells.
Cover with foil and bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until shells are tender and filling is set.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Stir well and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and stirring occasionally, simmer 10 minutes or until cranberry skins pop.
Remove from heat and let cool before transferring to serving bowl.
Chill thoroughly. Yields 4 cups.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes, adding all the ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Crumble topping (recipe to follow) on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick and easy jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour three 9-inch cake pans. Combine the cake mix, eggs, oil, and jam.
Mix well. Stir in the raisins and pecans.
Pour into the prepared pans. Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of the layers.
Remove from the pan and cool on a rack. Frost with Easy Caramel Frosting.

title: asilomar turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels, margarine and milk in double boiler.
It takes awhile.
Mix well and set aside.

title: apricot mold
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water and pour a little Jell-O into bottom of mold.
Add apricots, cut side up.
Freeze a few minutes.
Meanwhile, mix baby food with balance of Jell-O and chill (not too firm).
Add sour cream to mixture; blend together and strain.
Add rest of apricots, cut up, and pour into mold already set.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce until hot.
Remove from heat and stir in (dry) the large box of jello in hot applesauce.
Add crushed pineapple, then stir in 7-Up.
Mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch dish and chill until set.

title: so good casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion, salt and pepper.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with noodles; then add the layer of corn.
Pour soup over all and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: layered rainbow gelatin salad
directions: Mix together until dissolved.
Pour the clear layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan or deep sided glass bowl.
Chill until firm.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until very stiff. Beat in sugar, one tablespoon at a time and beat again until very stiff.
Do not underbeat!
Fold in almond extract, coconut and food coloring.
Drop and press mixture lightly and add a cherry half.
Bake at 300° until very light brown.

title: dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt with enough milk to make a sticky dough.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto beef stew and cook, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: holiday squares
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour batter into greased and floured 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet pan.
Make 28 squares.
Put 1 tablespoon cherry pie filling in the center of each square.
(You may use other fruit pie filling if you wish.)
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar on top when cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
When cool, top with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Pour in hot, boiling water.
Stir to consistency.
Deep fry in small amounts.
Will look like small pancakes when finished.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add cranberries and boil 5 to 10 minutes or until cranberry skins pop.
Remove from heat. Add gelatin, stirring 2 minutes or until jello dissolves. Stir in pineapple and nuts. Cover and chill 8 hours. Makes 4 cups.

title: spicy pineapple and zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until thick and foamy.
Add salad oil, sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in pineapple and zucchini and mix well. Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg. Mix well into wet mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Fold in gently until mixed.
Put in 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes and turn onto a rack and cool completely before slicing.

title: re-enlistment chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chicken and Provolone or Mozzarella cheese.
Pour over chicken; cover and marinate in refrigerator for at least one day.
Stir occasionally.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Before serving, sprinkle with the Mozzarella or Provolone cheese.

title: light fruitcake
directions: Combine brandy, orange juice and cranberries in large bowl. Cover mixture and let stand 1 hour.
Combine dates, pecans, orange rind, vanilla, eggs and pineapple.
Add to cranberry mixture. Stir well.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients.
Add to fruit mixture; stir well.
Spoon batter into a 6-cup Bundt pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted into cake comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool completely on wire rack. Bring 1/2 cup brandy to a boil; let cool.
Moisten several layers of cheesecloth in brandy and wrap cake in cheesecloth.
Cover with plastic wrap and then aluminum foil.
Store in a cool place at least 1 week before serving.
Yield: 16 servings (about 181 calories each).
Fat: 6 grams.

title: white corn casserole
directions: Combine and cook one hour at 350°.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf. Serves 4.

title: crustless pumpkin pie
directions: In large bowl, combine pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs and egg whites.
Beat until blended and smooth.
Mix in sugar, cinnamon, allspice, ginger and salt, blending well.
Stir in crumbs.
Spray high sided 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour pie filling into pie plate.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 45 to 55 minutes, until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool pie on wire rack; refrigerate overnight.
Cut in wedges; serve with small dollop of whipped cream.
Makes 10 servings.

title: lane's brunswick stew
directions: Cook meat until well done, then remove from bone.
(Meat cooked in pressure cooker is quicker and easier.)
Save broth from beef and chicken.
Put meat through grinder.
Peel onions and potatoes and put through grinder.
Put into broth and cook until done. (Corn and tomatoes should be run through grinder.)
Add meats, corn, tomato paste and tomatoes or juice to potatoes and onions. Add butter, barbecue sauce, Texas Pete and vinegar.
Add catsup last along with brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook until well blended and has desired taste.

title: apple walnut stuffing
directions: In large skillet, cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add water and bouillon; cook until bouillon dissolves. In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients; add celery mixture. Mix well.
Loosely stuff turkey just before roasting; place remaining stuffing in greased baking dish; bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: grilled sausage
directions: Soak sausage in water and vinegar mixture for at least 1/2 hour.
Then cook in microwave for 3 minutes.
Turn container and cook for an additional 3 minutes.
Drain water and vinegar from sausage and place on grill and cook until done.

title: crisco cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour, a little at a time, until all mixed in.
Add pecans, vanilla and salt and mix well.
Bake in 350° oven in Bundt pan for 1 hour.

title: freeze corn
directions: Take 2 pints of corn which has been cut off the cob and place in a saucepan with 3/4 pint of water, sugar and salt.
Bring to boil and cook for 5 to 7 minutes or until corn changes color. Cool and package and put in freezer; it will keep well for 1 year.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Bring tomato soup to a boil in saucepan; remove from heat.
Add cream cheese and gelatin to soup in blender; mix well.
Mix in celery, onion, shrimp and mayonnaise.
Pour in mold or round bottomed bowl.
Refrigerate until set.
Unmold onto platter.
Serve with crackers.

title: curried chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl except bread crumbs, butter and cheese.
Mix bread crumbs and butter in a small bowl.
Pour contents of large bowl into greased, 2-quart casserole.

Sprinkle with bread crumbs and then cheese. Bake, covered, at 350° until heated through (30 minutes to 1 hour), then remove lid and cook for an additional 10 minutes. Serve over rice or in pastry shells.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Open peaches and add sugar to them.
Turn oven to 350° and melt butter in oblong casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Remove dish with melted butter from oven and gently pour flour-sugar mixture in it.
Spoon peaches and syrup over top of mixture.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° until top is brown.

title: frozen hash browns
directions: Defrost potatoes and mix everything together except melted butter or oleo.
Place in a 3-quart casserole and sprinkle with corn flakes and melted butter or oleo.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: nutty strawberry bread
directions: Stir first 6 ingredients together; make a well in center. Combine oil, eggs, berries and nuts in a separate bowl; stir.
Pour this mixture into well.
Stir until moistened.
Dump into 2 greased bread pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: delicious bruschetta
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Gently spoon into chilled serving bowl.
Serve with bread or toast rounds.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut well.
Add onion, celery and green pepper and mix well.
Mix together in another bowl, sugar, vinegar and salad oil. Pour over kraut mixture.
Let stand overnight, preferably 24 hours.

title: shrimp, sausage and garlic cheese grits
directions: In a large stockpot, bring broth to a boil. Add butter. Pour grits into broth slowly and let cook on medium heat, stirring often. Cook about 10 minutes. Stir in salt and garlic powder. Cook on low heat until grits are starting to thicken. Add whipping cream slowly and stir until well blended. If grits thicken too much, add more broth.
While grits are cooking, place shrimp and sausage in a skillet with garlic, bourbon and Worcestershire sauce and saute until done. Then stir sausage and shrimp mixture into grits.
Add cheese and stir until well blended. Serves 12 to 15.

title: mex corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese, pour 1/2 of mix into skillet, spread cheese over mixture. Add remaining mix. Bake at 400 degrees for 35-40 minutes.

title: chops "a la jardinera"
directions: Trim off fat from chops.
Wash, drain and dry.
Mix and crush the next 5 ingredients.
Rub chops with this mixture.
In a heavy kettle or skillet, brown chops lightly.
Add the tomatoes, onions, bay leaf, 1 teaspoon salt, green peppers and carrots (including liquid from tomatoes).
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Cover; turn heat to medium.
Boil for 30 minutes.
Uncover; boil for 20 to 30 minutes more.
Drain the string beans and corn; add to the mixture.
Boil for 10 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Layer potatoes in baking dish; sprinkle with flour.
Dot with butter and sprinkle seasonings. Repeat layers.
Pour in milk until it comes up on the sides of dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beet pickles
directions: *Choose young beets as nearly same size as possible.
If some are much larger than others, the larger ones may be cut in half (halves) or quarters after cooking and peeling.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix all together using enough milk to make a soft dough.
Roll out and cut into squares.
Peel and quarter 10 to 12 medium apples.
Place enough apples in each dough to have room to fold corners.
Place in a deep dish.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon of the salt.
Gradually stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Cool mixture to room temperature.
Bring water, remaining 2 teaspoons sat and oil to a boil.
Add pasta.
Cook at rolling boil until pasta is done. Drain pasta, rinse and cool.
Combine egg mixture and pasta.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight in airtight container.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: crisp cheese bites
directions: Do not substitute for butter.

title: "ice cream"-coconut-caramel pies
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in coconut and pecans. Toast lightly, stirring frequently until coconut is golden.
Cool completely.
Beat cheese and milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread 1/4 cheese mixture into each pie shell.
Drizzle 1/4 of caramel over each pie.
Sprinkle 1/4 of coconut mixture over each pie.
Repeat layers, cover well and freeze until firm.
Let pies stand 5 minutes at room temperature before slicing.

title: linzer torte
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add yolks, almonds and flavorings. Add flour and baking powder; mix well and fold in stiffly beaten whites.
Roll out or pat 2/3 dough in greased and floured spring-form pan, having the dough thicker on the bottom than on the sides.
Fill with jam or preserves.
Roll out rest of dough; cut in strips and crisscross over top.
Bake for 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: whole turkey deep fried
directions: Dissolve red pepper in salt.
Fry turkey in peanut oil.
Use large pan or pot to hold turkey.
Inject turkey every 2 or 3 inches all around.
Season all around to taste.
Wrap the drumsticks together with a wire or coat hanger so you can pull it out of grease.
Your grease should be at 350° when you drop bird in.
An average bird will take about 45 minutes to brown and cook. It will come to the surface when cooked.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute frozen chopped broccoli in 4 tablespoons butter.
Add chopped onions and celery and saute.
Mix vegetables, rice, soup, water, milk and Cheez Whiz well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
You may use more rice.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds, mixing until well blended.
Spoon mixture into 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Simmer butter, onion and broccoli, stirring occasionally.
Once broccoli is soft, add milk, soup and cheese. Cook until all cheese is melted.
Be sure to stir.
Add rice. Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or microwave on High for 10 minutes, rotating after the first 5 minutes.
This will thicken as it cools.

title: mama g's buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients with shortening. Add milk. On a floured surface, roll out until approximately 1/4-inch thick. Cut with a floured cutter. (I use a drinking glass because it's easier and less messy.) Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Cook at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown beef.
Cook macaroni.
Place in layers in large casserole beef, tomato sauce, macaroni; repeat.
Place cheese over all. Cover with pizza sauce.
Bake, covered, about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and chop apples and set aside.
Measure salad oil into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add a small amount of flour at a time, with chopped nuts and apples.
The batter will be stiff.
Bake in a 350° oven in greased and floured pan, 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
This cake can be served with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender except coconut.
Blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into a 9-inch greased pie pan. Let stand 5 minutes; sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This pie forms its own crust.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: jello cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add jello, eggs and vanilla flavoring.
Stir in milk and add flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pink puff
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together. Stir boiling water and jello together until dissolved. Blend jello with cream cheese mixture until smooth. Add fruit and nuts. Fold in cool whip and refrigerate.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Add milk all at once; cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: lemon cream cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix using the package directions for two eight inch cake pans.
Cool as directed.
Mix half the condensed milk and half the lemon juice in a bowl.
Spread between the cake layers.
Mix the remaining condensed milk, remaining lemon juice and the whipped topping in a bowl.
Spread over the top and side of the cake.
Chill until serving time.

title: grandma sherman's sponge cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cook in slow oven (250°) for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: egyptian salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add marshmallows. Add cut-up cherries, drained pineapple and whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Add nuts.
Chill covered overnight.

title: creamy fruit dressing or dip
directions: Blend well.
You'll have 1 1/2 cups to pour over fruit salad or for dip.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a crust.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broken glass salad
directions: Prepare orange, cherry and lime jello by using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water per package.
Pour each in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Dissolve lemon jello and sugar in boiling pineapple juice.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Prepare 2 packages Dream Whip as directed. Fold into whipped lemon jello.
Cut orange, cherry and lime jello into cubes.
Fold all together and chill.
Can use as a dessert using a graham cracker crumb crust.

title: pizza ryes
directions: Brown meats; drain fat and add cubed cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Spread on party rye; sprinkle with oregano. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: squash drumsticks
directions: Cook squash with onion in water until tender.
Dip in beaten egg and milk.
Coat with cracker crumbs and deep fry until golden brown.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, pecans and strawberries.
Stir until moistened.
Spoon in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape in balls. Brown in 2 tablespoons oil.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix meal, sour cream, 1 tablespoon of sugar and egg.
Bake, cool and crumble.
Mix remaining ingredients with crumbs and chill before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese, chop dried beef and onions, mix all together.
Roll into ball.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Cook package of pilaf as per box instructions.
In large casserole dish mix all ingredients and level out in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spiced pumpkin bars
directions: In a medium bowl stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, and salt;
set aside.
In a large mixing bowl beat together eggs, pumpkin, sugar and oil with electric mixer on medium speed.
Add the flour mixture;
beat until well combined.
Stir in chopped pecans and spread batter into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool completely in pan on a wire rack.
In a medium mixing bowl beat together the cream cheese, butter, and vanilla until fluffy.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until smooth.
Frost pumpkin bars.

title: grandma bell's beet pickles
directions: Wash beets, leaving on roots and 1-inch of tops.
Cover beets with boiling water and simmer until tender (about 25 minutes). Drain, slip off skins and trim beets.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Cook and drain mostaccioli.
Mix with salad oil while warm. Mix together sugar, cider vinegar, seasonings and parsley flakes and add to mostaccioli.
Marinate overnight, stirring periodically.
Gradually add onion, cucumber and green pepper, stirring after each addition.
Add tomato, olives and cheese just before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Great for cookouts!

title: easy banana pie
directions: Slice bananas and line the bottom and sides of pie crusts.
Mix cream cheese with 1 cup of milk.
Add instant vanilla pudding powder and another cup of milk.
Pour on top of bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate about an hour before serving.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keeps in refrigerator for 6 weeks.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: new orleans crab cakes
directions: Saute onion, peppers, scallions and garlic in butter for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add parsley, thyme, Bechamel sauce, bread, salt and cayenne pepper.
Mix all and cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Take off the fire and when cool, form the mixture into 2-inch cakes.
Roll in bread crumbs and saute in olive oil until golden brown.
Serve hot with a cold cucumber dill sauce.
Serves 12.
Bon appetit.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Place in a baking dish.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
In a saucepan over medium heat, combine pineapple juice, cranberry sauce, vinegar, brown sugar and broth.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Stir until smooth.
Add to sauce mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Add pineapple chunks and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 35 minutes.
Add pepper strips.
Bake another 5 minutes.

title: zucchini cake with caramel frosting
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Cream next 5 ingredients together.
Combine the 2 mixtures together.
Gradually add zucchini, nuts and chips.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Combine cream cheese, can of condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Pour in graham cracker pie crust.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top next day with cherry filling (or any fruit that you prefer.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Prepare potatoes by boiling (until fork slides out easily). Let cool, peel and slice.

Prepare onions by thinly slicing them and then salting them with approximately 3 tablespoons of salt. Let onions sit for at least 20 minutes, until they are limp. Rinse with water (two times) and drain.
Mix all ingredients. Pepper to taste (and can pepper the top for a finished look). Enjoy!
Yields 5 to 10 servings.

title: orange sherbet punch
directions: In large bowl, mix orange pop, Seven-Up, frozen orange juice and lemon juice together.
Pour into punch bowl; float scoops of sherbet on top.
Add ice cubes with cherries for color.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pans.
Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Stir 50 to 75 strokes by hand until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into loaf pans.
Sprinkle and pat almonds on loaf.
Bake at 350°.
Cool in pans on rack for 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely before serving.

title: chicken with mushroom gravy(low calorie - 230 calories)
directions: Place skinned chicken in a heated skillet treated with vegetable spray-on.
Brown chicken.
Pour tomato juice and mushroom liquid over chicken; stir in onion, parsley, salt, basil leaves and garlic powder.
Cover and simmer about 60 minutes or until chicken is done.
Stir in mushrooms.
Mix cornstarch and water and stir into liquid in skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Serves 6.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplants until tender; drain.
Mix all of the ingredients (use only 1 cup of Velveeta cheese with mixture). Pour into casserole and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on top and bake until melted.

title: heart healthy meat loaf
directions: Mix milk and oats.
Add turkey, eggs, garlic, pepper, chili powder and chopped onion.
Form into meat loaf.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° 1 1/2 hours until done.

title: mexican franks
directions: Fry tortillas 1 at a time in 1/4-inch hot oil for 3 to 5 seconds on each side or just until softened.
Drain on paper towels; set aside.
Combine chili, 1/4 cup tomato sauce, onion and hot sauce.
Place a frankfurter in center of each tortilla; top with 2 tablespoons chili mixture.
Roll up and place seam side down in lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Repeat procedure with remaining tortillas; set aside.
Combine remaining tomato sauce and remaining chili mixture; pour over tortillas. Sprinkle with chiles.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle with cheese; bake 5 additional minutes. Yields 10 servings.

title: lorna doone dessert
directions: Crush Lorna Doones.
Melt butter and mix together with crushed Lorna Doones.
Press in bottom of an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix puddings and milk, then add softened ice cream.
Put on top of cookie mix.
Let set in fridge until firm.
Then put Cool Whip on top of ice cream mixture; put back in fridge for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle with Heath bar bits just before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fruit salad
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, flour and eggs.
Gradually add milk to mixture and cook over medium heat until it makes a thin pudding. Add vanilla.
Peel and slice fruit into pieces and add to pudding when it is cool.
Top with coconut and chopped pecans.

title: red bean rice
directions: Brown sausage.
Add tomatoes, water, onion and kidney beans. Cook for awhile.
Add rice mix.
Cook until thickened.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Garnish with maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In crock-pot, layer beef cubes, onion and paprika to make 3 equal layers.
Put on high with lid on, approximately 6 to 8 hours.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Add to meat.
Add eggs and sour cream and mix well.
Continue on high until well heated.
Serve.

title: ham croquettes
directions: Grind 1 pound of lean ham.
Grate cheese; mix with mayonnaise. Season with grated onion, Worcestershire sauce, paprika, Tabasco sauce, black pepper and chopped nuts.
Let stand in refrigerator for 12 hours.

title: linda's punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Cool and combine with remaining ingredients.
Add enough water to make 2 gallons of punch.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash avocados and blend in ingredients in order given.
Stir or blend well.
Serve with chips or party crackers.
Serves 8.

title: easy cream cheese bars
directions: Unroll the first crescent roll dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan and press dough to fit the pan, pressing perforated lines, making sure they stick together.
Then mix cream cheese with sugar, vanilla and lemon juice (add a couple of drops of milk if cream cheese mixture is extra thick).
Pour mixture over dough.

title: potato-ham casserole
directions: Spread hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ham over potatoes.
Mix sour cream and soup together; spread over potatoes and ham.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together with mixer at medium speed. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: plum cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix oil and sugar, then add eggs one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients; add plums and nuts.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 325° for 55 to 75 minutes.
Test for doneness between those times.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix all together and chill before serving.

title: toasted parsnips
directions: Peel the parsnips.
Cut them into 2-inch lengths across the grain.
Cut the lengths down into quarters or eighths.
Boil them in salted water until tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain them thoroughly and put a folded cloth on top of the saucepan to enable the parsnips to dry off.
Melt the butter in the frying pan.
Toss in the cooked parsnips, sprinkled with the sugar.
Pepper well and brown on all sides.
Or you could put the buttered parsnips under the broiler and toast.
Nice with roast beef.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: quick shrimp curry(servings:  4)
directions: Cook rice; simmer the onions and curry powder in the butter in the top part of a double boiler until onions are tender, but not brown.
Add the frozen soup; set pan over hot water and stir until smooth.
Stir in the shrimp, sour cream and dash of lemon juice and heat well.
Serve immediately over cooked rice or combine in a casserole and keep warm in the oven until time to serve.

title: baked apples
directions: Core 1 apple; sprinkle with cinnamon, brown sugar and nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Grease 8-inch round cake pan.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt; blend well.
Cut in 1/4 cup margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in raisins and caraway seeds, if desired. Add milk all at once.
Knead dough gently until no longer sticky, 5 to 6 times.
Press dough into pan, cut cross on top of loaf.
Brush with melted margarine.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately. Cool completely.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Dice first 5 ingredients very fine.
Saute in margarine and olive oil until onions are clear looking, on low temperature, about 2 hours.
Add stewed tomatoes and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Let boil on low heat about 2 hours.
Add Worcestershire sauce, red pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Stir often for two or more hours.

title: my own ice cream
directions: You will need 1 small can, 1 large can and 1 big spoon.

title: three-cheese chicken bake
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Remove from heat. Stir in soup, mushrooms, pimentos and basil; set aside.

title: onion casserole
directions: Partially cook bacon pieces.
Remove.
Add onion rings to bacon fat.
Saute until soft.
Add onions to bacon.
Melt butter in a large casserole dish.
Add crumbs to butter; mix.
Pat mixture up sides of casserole dish and cover bottom.
Line with grated cheese.
Add bacon and onion mixture.
Combine eggs and milk.
Pour over all.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Set aside nuts.
Add all ingredients to softened cream cheese and chill.
When well chilled, shape into a ball or log and roll in chopped nuts.
Keep chilled until served.

title: grill cheese and tomato soup
directions: Grill cheese sandwiches in skillet with butter.
Add tomato soup, milk and butter in saucepan and cook for 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Note:
Approximately 2 large potatoes or 18 ounce can Tartan sweet potatoes.

title: chicken breasts capri
directions: Rub the breasts with the cut lemon, squeezing the lemon as you rub.
Sprinkle
salt
and
pepper over the chicken and coat with flour.
Heat butter in electric skillet to 300° and brown chicken breasts
in
butter.
Mix
the soup, sherry and cheese and
pour over
browned
chicken.
Simmer
at 225° for about 1
hour.* Remove
chicken
to
warm serving platter and spoon
gravy
over chicken.
Garnish with parsley and/or lemon peel roses.
Serves 4.
Serve with wild rice, green vegetable and congealed fruit salad.

title: pink salmon loaf
directions: Mix together.
Cool in refrigerator.
Roll in pecan pieces in a long roll with wax paper or shape in a loaf pan.
Serve with crackers.

title: zucchini sweet relish
directions: Combine zucchini, peppers and onions.
Sprinkle with salt. Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, rinse well (cold water) and drain well.
Add spices, vinegar, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook gently 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized jars.
Seal immediately.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix
oil,
sugar,
eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; mix
well.	Add
fruit and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.	Cool.

title: five-flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add flavorings; beat well.
Beat in eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with evaporated milk.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: chop suey
directions: *May substitute 2 pounds cubed beef.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Melt all this in double boiler; let cool.
Fold in 1/2 pint whipping cream that has been whipped.
Pour into pie crust and set in icebox to cool.

title: orange jello salad
directions: In bowl combine
dry
Jell-O
with cottage cheese, Cool Whip, pineapple and fruit.
Mix together and chill.

title: dill bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine in mixing bowl the cottage cheese, sugar, onion, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and softened yeast.
Add flour to form stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Cover.
Let rise until light and doubled in size (50 or 60 minutes).
Stir down dough and turn into warmed greased 8-inch round casserole (2-quart) or 2 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Let rise in warm place until light, 30 or 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Brush with butter and salt.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix together sour cream, marshmallows and coconut.
Fold in fruit.
Decorate with maraschino cherries.
Chill.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine butter, sugar, cocoa and milk; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Allow to come to a rapid boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, peanut butter, coconut and oats.
Spread in thin layer.
Let stand 2 hours.
Cut and serve.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
In small bowl, beat eggs and add sausage.
Pour into skillet; cook until done.
Fill tortillas with the eggs and top with cheese and picante sauce.
Roll up and eat.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients.
Make meatballs in large walnut size and brown in skillet.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: On lightly floured surface, roll out 1/2 of pastry into an 11-inch circle.
Use to line a 9-inch pie plate; trim. Refrigerate, with rest of pastry, until ready to use.

title: no fail caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter; add sugars. Boil on low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.

Add milk and keep stirring until mixture boils. Remove from heat. Add vanilla extract; let cool thoroughly, then add confectioners sugar. Spread on cool cake. (If margarine is used, use a good grade such as Parkay.)

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water, refrigerate.
Wash cranberries.
Wash and pare (not all peeling) 2 apples, and remove core.
Peel 2 oranges, remove seeds. Grind cranberries, apples and oranges in food grinder (medium grinder).
Add 1 1/2 cups of sugar and 1 cup nuts and mix well. Add to Jello and let set.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs, oil, juice and vanilla at high speed for 10 minutes.
Next, blend in flour, baking powder and salt, a little at a time, after these have been sifted together. Stir in nuts.

title: pea and vegetable salad
directions: Drain juice from the first 5 ingredients.
Chop the pepper, celery and green onions finely.

title: covered nuts
directions: Cook together until soft ball stage.
Cool slightly.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: pizza mac casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
While warm, add Velveeta, then add water and stir.
When browning sausage, drain the grease and add to macaroni.
Add salt and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Top with mushrooms.
Top with grated cheeses and sprinkle with pizza topping.
Before baking, add milk and melted butter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hungarian coffee cake
directions: Mix by hand like pie crust then take out 1 1/2 cups for top of cake.
Set aside.
Add to mixture left; 1/2 teaspoon baking soda in 1 cup of buttermilk or sour milk.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add nutmeg and cinnamon to crumbs; add to top of cake.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple stack cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening well. Add eggs, then buttermilk to which soda has been added. Sift flour, salt and spices together and add to first mixture. You may need more or less flour. Chill in the refrigerator so it can be handled. Turn into floured bowl. Separate into 6 portions. Cut bottom liners for round cake pans. Roll onto liners. Place in pan. Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Spread sweetened apples between layers.

title: beef macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain.
Sprinkle Tabasco and salt over ground beef.
Saute until partly brown.
Add onions.
In 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of macaroni and meat.
Stir chili powder and oregano into stewed tomatoes and pour over top.
Heat at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: orange bread
directions: Open biscuit packages; separate biscuits.
Combine melted butter, sugar and orange rind.
Dip biscuits, one at a time, in mixture and place on end in a Bundt pan; should fill all around the pan ring.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Dump out immediately on plate and serve.
Delicious with a luncheon chicken salad.

title: apple raisin pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops with flour.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt. Brown on both sides in oil in a large skillet.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water; pour over chops.
Cut apples into 1/2-inch wedges. Place apple wedges on pork chops.
Sprinkle raisins over all. Cover and boil gently about 25 minutes or until chops are tender. Remove chops to heated platter.
Combine flour and a small amount of Carnation to make a paste.
Gradually stir in remaining Carnation and remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add to drippings in skillet, stirring over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil and thickens.
Serve over pork chops.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together; beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add flour.
Beat in lemon extract and cold 7-Up.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool 15 to 20 minutes and take out of pan.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from meat; cut meat into strips.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add meat; cook, turning frequently, until brown, about 5 minutes.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes for round steak and 5 to 8 minutes for sirloin.
Add pepper strips during last 5 minutes of simmering.
While meat simmers, cook rice as directed for 4 to 6 servings.

title: kahlua
directions: Drop bean into 1 gallon container.
Mix 4 cups sugar in 3 cups water.
Mix 1/2 cup coffee with boiling water.
Pour mixtures above and vodka in container and cover.
Let stand 2 weeks at room temperature.
Gently mix occasionally.
Strain through cloth to remove specks of bean, if desired.

title: enchiladas
directions: Fry ground beef in pan (chop in small pieces).
Mix beef with all the ingredients and 1 cup each of the 2 cheeses.
Fill tortillas with about 2 spoonfuls.
Make sure pans are greased before rolling enchiladas.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Five minutes before taking out, sprinkle Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese over them.
Take out when melted.

title: seafood linguini
directions: Drain clams and shrimp (save juice).
Saute scallops in butter until lightly brown.
Add clams, shrimp, mushrooms, chopped green ends of the onions, 2 tablespoons garlic and 1 cup of wine.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add 1/2 of saved juice.
Cover and keep warm.
Boil noodles.
Use half and half, flour and saved juice. Heat in skillet together to make white sauce.

title: lasagna florentine
directions: In a large pan, cook onion and garlic in oil.
Add pasta sauce; simmer 15 minutes.
In a bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, spinach, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
In a 15 x 9-inch baking dish, layer 2 cups sauce, half the lasagna, half the remaining sauce, all of spinach mixture, half the Mozzarella cheese, remaining lasagna and sauce.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot.
Uncover; top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Top with parsley, if desired.

title: orange pudding
directions: Mix sugar, juice and egg yolks; beat with beater.
Mix gelatin with a little cold water, then add boiling water.
Mix all together.
Whip heavy cream and fold into the mixture.
Store in cold place until set.

title: amaretto fruit dip
directions: Mix together pudding and Cool Whip.
Add Amaretto, starting with 1/4 cup and adding to taste.
Serve chilled with fresh fruit.

title: jello pie
directions: Add Cool Whip to jello.
Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Add nuts if desired.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: In large pan, brown onion in fat.
Add hamburger meat; cook until well done.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: lime mousse dessert in punch bowl
directions: Whip cream and refrigerate.
Soften gelatin in water.
Heat slowly to dissolve and cool.
Add juice.
Beat egg yolks with sugar.
Blend in juice and gelatin mixture.
Whip egg whites and stir in cream.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Cook
green pepper and onions in butter, then add flour and seasonings	to
green
pepper.
This prevents pepper from going to the
bottom of casserole.	Then add corn, milk and 1 dozen crackers,
then
add remaining crackers on top and cook until firm.
Serves about 6.

title: greek cheese
directions: Bring all ingredients to room temperature and combine in mixer. (Do not use blender or processor.)
Allow time for flavors to blend.
Serve with crackers, toast or hot bread.
Makes 12 servings.

title: garlic salad croutons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toss croutons in melted butter; sprinkle with garlic powder and sesame seed, if desired.
Place in a single layer on baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool thoroughly before storing in an airtight container.

title: german crumb cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and cut in shortening to crumb stage. Reserve 1 cup of this mixture.
Add all dry ingredients, then eggs and sour milk.
Pour into shallow pan (5 x 9-inch or 8 x 8-inch).
Sprinkle top with the cup of reserved mixture.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 40 minutes.

title: fudge nut brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease cookie sheets.
In a large bowl, combine brownie mix, flour, water, oil and egg.
Stir with spoon until dough is formed.
(I use electric beater on low.) Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Cool completely.
Frost cookies, if desired, with chocolate frosting.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: dirt cups
directions: Make pudding mix as directed.
Stir whipped topping and 1/2 of the crushed cookies into pudding until mixture is the same color. Place 1 tablespoon of crushed cookies into bottom of each paper cup.
Fill cups 3/4 full of pudding.
Top each cup with the rest of cookies.
Put in refrigerator to chill, about 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 dirt cups.

title: hot pizza sandwiches
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Drain.
Mix in cheese over low heat until melted.
Add all other ingredients and spread on bread slices.
Quick freeze on pan in freezer for 5 minutes.
Take out and place in freezer bags until ready to serve. When ready to eat, heat on cookie sheet in oven at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: cheese and vegetable casserole
directions: Thaw and cook vegetables about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine vegetables, soup, sour cream, pepper, 1/2 cup cheese and half a can of onions.
Pour into baking dish and bake covered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Remove cover, add remaining cheese and onions and bake uncovered for 5 - 10 minutes.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ice cream jello delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; reserve 1/2 of this mixture.
Add syrup from mandarins to remaining Jell-O.
Chill until partially set; fold in mandarins, bananas and pecans.
Turn into 6 cup bowl or into 10 or 12 individual molds; chill until almost set.
Add vanilla ice cream by spoonfuls to reserved hot Jell-O; stir until melted.
Chill until mixture mounds on spoon; fold in banana mixture.
Spoon ice cream and jello mixture over fruit and Jell-O mixture.
Chill.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: braunschweiger party log
directions: Remove film from braunschweiger, taking care to retain meat in its log shape.
Frost log with cream cheese and roll in bacon bits.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in a large skillet. Drain any excess grease. Add all of the ingredients except cheese. Simmer 10 minutes. Top with cheese. When cheese is melted, serve while hot.

title: cheesy chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chopped chicken, cream of chicken soup and 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese. Stir until melted and blended. Spoon mixture onto tortilla.
