Roll up and place seam side down in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with 1 jar of salsa and shredded Mexican cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 6.

title: great grandmother's gingerbread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg, molasses and then dry ingredients. Add hot water last and beat until smooth.
Bake in a greased shallow pan for 40 to 45 minutes in moderate oven at 350°.
Yields 15 portions.

title: dream cheese pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package.
In another bowl, blend cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Spoon into pie shell and chill for 3 hours.
Spoon on pie filling.

title: strawberry bread with spread
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup strawberry juice for spread.
Mix all dry ingredients together.

Make a hole in the center of the mixture. Pour strawberries, oil and eggs into the hole. Mix by hand until all ingredients are thoroughly combined. Add food coloring. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool.

title: saucy ham and potato
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk.
Cook stirring constantly until thickened. Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Toss with potatoes in cheese sauce.
Add ham.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oriental balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 400° oven, then place in slow cooker and cover with sweet and sour sauce.
Serve while warm.

title: crab souffle(mock)
directions: Remove crusts from fresh white bread and make cubes.
Mix all ingredients except breadcrumbs and put into buttered casserole. Sprinkle breadcrumbs over top.
Bake 1 hour uncovered.
After the first 1/2 hour of cooking, stir well.
Casserole provides for 8 people and is good accompanied by spiced peaches.

title: summer lime chicken breasts
directions: Pound out breasts between wax paper to flatten slightly. Combine all ingredients and marinate for 1 hour.
Grill chicken on barbecue for 2 minutes each side.

title: tortilla surprise
directions: Bake ribs in casserole dish with 1/4 cup vinegar and water to cover at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until done.
Drain liquid; remove all excess fat.
Peel and slice apples into wedges.
Slice cheese.
Roll apple, cheese and pork in a soft tortilla shell by Mex America.
Secure with toothpick.
Bake for about 15 minutes at 350°, or until shell is brown and cheese melts.
Top with sour cream and/or hot sauce.
Garnish can be black olives, peppers or lettuce.

title: cookies
directions: Tear bread into small pieces.
Mix together with other ingredients in food processor.
Drop onto cookie sheet from spoon. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
For extra flavoring, use any extracts such as vanilla extract, almond extract, black walnut extract or banana extract.
Cinnamon is also good and butter flavoring may be added to any for a richer flavor.
Makes 1 serving.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Shred or chop cabbage. Cut bell pepper into small pieces. Grate carrot. Mix and set aside. Boil remaining ingredients. Pour over slaw. Let stand until cool. Refrigerate. Keeps well.

title: orange cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together two times.
Cream margarine. Add eggs, gradually add flour/sugar mixture and milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake on 350° in 3 or 4 layers until tests done.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cut cooked potatoes in half.
Scoop out meat of the potato and whip with margarine and milk.
Mound back into the potato halves.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onion and celery in margarine.
Combine all ingredients and place in greased 2-quart casserole. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool 45 minutes.

title: royal plum pudding
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in apple, raisins, pineapple, pecans, dates and currants. Pour into a 4 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold; serve with Brandy Hard Sauce.

title: italian sausage sauce for spaghetti
directions: Cut sausage into 1-inch pieces.
Cook in large pan in 1/4 cup water until water evaporates and sausage begins to brown, about 10 minutes.
Add onion and parsley and cook until it's yellow.
Add 1/4 cup water and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling point and simmer, uncovered, 1 1/4 hours stirring occasionally.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on a 10 to 12-inch serving dish.
Spread shrimp on cream cheese, then spread cocktail sauce over shrimp. Sprinkle cheese over shrimp and top with green onions.
Serve with crackers.

title: skillet pasta
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and water to meat. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; stir in pasta.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Stir in Ricotta cheese.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 Mozzarella cheese; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover and let stand until cheese is melted.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Work together butter and cheese; add flour, Rice Krispies and pepper.
Form into balls; place on cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake 12 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Let cool.
Top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: jell-o jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl at least 3 minutes until completely dissolved. Pour into 13 X 9-inch pan or molds. Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until firm (does not stick to finger when touched).

title: poppy's easter eggs
directions: Cream the butter and cheese.
Use at room temperature.
Sift in 10x sugar to creamed mix, then add coconut, salt and vanilla. Refrigerate batch for 1 hour.
Remove from refrigerator and shape into small size, about 1 1/2-inch size eggs.
Place on wax paper tray and refrigerate again for 1 hour.
Melt wax in a double boiler, then melt chocolate. Dip eggs in chocolate.
Use icepick or skewer.
Place on wax paper.
Makes about 120 eggs.

title: delicious chicken
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish put a layer of dried beef.
Put chicken on top of dried beef.
Lay sliced cheese on top of chicken. Combine soups and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: humble log cabbage stew
directions: Brown up
the
beef,
then throw in the onions, cabbage and celery.
Cook
until
yellowish, then add 2 cups water and simmer for
around 15 minutes.
Slip in the rest of the ingredients and continue cooking for 15 to 20 minutes. To give stew a continental look, serve it on top of mashed potatoes.
The 2 cups water may not be necessary,
if
there is plenty of juice in the canned beans and tomatoes.

title: coconut surprises
directions: Work cheese with spoon until light and fluffy. Thoroughly mix in Sweet 'N Low, grated rinds and walnuts. Form into 12 balls about 1 inch in diameter (8 grams). Roll in toasted coconut. Refrigerate. Makes 12. One Coconut Surprise has 35 calories.

title: soft gingersnaps
directions: Whip cream.
Add remaining ingredients except flour.
Stir 10 minutes.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
May be rolled 1/4-inch and cut into shapes.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Brush with water before baking in 300° oven.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes.
Leave on cookie sheet to cool. Decorate if desired.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs together.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder in a separate bowl.
Add a small amount of flour mixture at a time into other mixture, until all is mixed.
Then add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ole fashioned raisin pie
directions: Boil the raisins, water and sugar, then stir in flour (diluted with water).
Let cook until thickened.
Add butter and vinegar. Bake between two crusts for 45 minutes at 450° for first 10 minutes, then finish at 350° until crust is golden brown.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar and Karo 1 minute.
Add to corn flakes and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Mash potato while still warm.
Mix in vanilla.
Mix enough 10x sugar with potato to make it stiff enough to roll out.
Roll out and spread with peanut butter.
Roll up (like a jelly roll) and chill.
Slice and serve.

title: french toast
directions: Melt butter in a jelly roll pan. Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over butter in pan. Mix eggs and orange juice. Dip bread slices in egg/juice mixture and place over mixture in jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes per side.

title: oreo peanut ice cream dessert
directions: Combine Oreos and 1/2 cup butter.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Soften vanilla ice cream and spread over cookie mixture; sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups of Spanish peanuts.
Freeze.

title: chocolate peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk. Bring to a full rolling boil. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. After removing the hot mixture from the stove, dissolve the peanut butter in it.
If you use pecans, put them in the oats.
Pour mixture over the oats and pecans, stirring. Drop from spoon on waxed paper.

title: turkey meat balls with rice or egg noodles
directions: Combine egg, turkey, crumbs, onion, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon tarragon, 3/4 teaspoon salt, lemon rind and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. With tablespoon, shape into 40 balls.
Brown half of meat balls in 2 1/2 tablespoons oil in large skillet 6 minutes.
Remove to platter.
Brown remainder.
Saute mushrooms in remaining oil in skillet 2 minutes; add to meat balls.
Add broth, lemon juice, rest of tarragon, salt and pepper to skillet.
Boil 1 or 2 minutes.
Return meat balls and mushrooms to skillet.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Add package turkey gravy (optional).

title: caramel filling
directions: Boil all the ingredients except vanilla, about 15 minutes. Remove from fire.
Add vanilla and beat until it begins to thicken.
Spread between cake layers and on top.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly the meat, onion and egg.
Press in a casserole dish.
Spread soup over top of meat mixture.
Then place Tater Tots on top of soup.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: special chicken or home baked fish sticks
directions: You will need waxed paper, bowl, small saucepan, baking pan, spatula and a grown-up with knife.

title: cheesecake
directions: Line bottom and sides of spring-form pan with ladyfingers, the outside of the ladyfingers against the pan.
In a large bowl, whip all other ingredients about 5 minutes at high speed.
Pour mixture into pan and refrigerate overnight.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
After cake has set overnight, then add the can of cherries, blueberries, etc.

title: yellow squash muffins(easy and yummy)
directions: Mix warm squash with melted butter and egg.
Combine flour and other ingredients.
Stir in squash mixture just until moistened.
Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: garden green beans with bacon
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, place beans and bacon.
Add enough water to cover.
Bring to a full boil.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until beans are crisp-tender (20 to 25 minutes). Drain.
Return to pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until onion is crisp-tender (5 to 7 minutes).
Yields 6 servings.

title: my omi's honig kuchen(honey cakes)
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Take small amounts of batter and roll out on floured board to a thickness of 1/8-inch.
Cut out with cookie cutters and bake at 350° until light and puffy.
Makes a lot of cookies.
Placed in a large cookie tin, will store indefinitely.
In fact, the older they get the chewier. On a cold day just before Christmas, they are the best.

title: christmas rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into 2 round pans.
Bake as directed.
Remove cake from pans.
Place cake layers back into the pans (after cleaning pans).
Prick each layer with fork.
Spoon prepared red Jello over 1 layer and prepared lime Jello over the other layer.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Remove cake with Jello from pans by dipping pan into warm water for 10 seconds. Invert onto cake plate.
Spread first layer with Cool Whip.
Remove second layer from pan and place on top of first layer.
Frost with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Top may be decorated with candy.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour in sugar, butter and milk.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: orange ice cream punch
directions: Beat together ice cream and Hawaiian Punch until smooth. Slowly stir in club soda.
Serve in glasses with straws.
Make this punch just before serving, as it separates as it stands. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: lemon or vanilla chocolate chip yogurt bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Then add chocolate chips.
Cream together eggs, oil and sugar.
Then add yogurt and extract.
Mix all ingredients well in large bowl.
Spoon into 2 loaf pans and bake 1 hour.
Cool on racks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, eggs, onion, soup, mayonnaise and Cheddar cheese together.
Top with stuffing and pour butter over it.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ranch beans
directions: Fry hamburger and drain off grease.
Pour all ingredients into large kettle and simmer 45 minutes.

title: tomato and basil fettuccine salad
directions: Prepare pasta according to directions.
Toss with oil, vinegar and cheese.
Add basil and tomatoes.
Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste.
Serve.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add onion and milk.
Let set 10 minutes. Drop into hot fish grease.
When golden brown, remove and drain.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all but dressing.
Stir in dressing thoroughly.
Add less or more as desired.
Serve immediately or chill briefly. Preparation time: 5 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain vegetables.
In baking dish, mix vegetables, 3/4 of cracker crumbs, cheese and mayonnaise together.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Serves approximately 5 people.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Slice zucchini thin, about 2 to 3 cups.
Add eggs, chopped onions, Bisquick and oil.
Add salt, parsley, pepper, garlic powder and cheese.
Place in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: Separate dough into 4 rectangles; press perforations together. Place 8 pepperoni on each rectangle.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons Mozzarella cheese over pepperoni.
Roll up tightly.
Slice each roll into 1-inch slices.
Bake on ungreased pan 18 to 20 minutes. Serve with pizza sauce.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish, lightly sprayed with Pam.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown on top.

title: marie's barbecue fish on outside grill
directions: Place fish on a large square piece of foil.
Cover top with crumbs.
Sprinkle soy sauce and lemon juice on top of crumbs.
Dot each piece with butter or margarine.
Close foil and place on hot coals 10 minutes.
(Can be done in 350° oven for 15 minutes.) Yield:
4 servings.

title: mud bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In first bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In second bowl, beat brown sugar, butter and vanilla until creamy.
Add egg; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture from first bowl.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups chocolate chips, nuts and coconut.
Spread into foil lined 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: squash fritters
directions: Beat eggs in deep bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and fry in hot pan with small amount of vegetable oil.
Add more if needed.
Use one or more tablespoons mixture for each fritter.
Keep fritters warm in oven while frying.
Serve with margarine or can be served with pancake syrup.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll dough out, cut with round cutter or glass about 2 3/4 inches across.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook the pie crusts.
Mix remaining ingredients well, pour into pie shells and refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown beef, onion, garlic salt and pepper in skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Put in crock-pot with all other ingredients and stir.
Cook on low for 5 to 6 hours.

title: red rice
directions: In a saucepan, cook bacon unti brown.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Cook until these are transparent.
Add tomato choice, spices, bay leaf, sugar and simmer until bubbly.
Add this mixture to the rice.
(A rice steamer is the best cooker for this, but a large pot can be used.)
Cook about 45 minutes, stirring well twice.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corned beef vegetable soup
directions: Put can of corned beef, 6 cups water and onion on and boil until corned beef blends into water and onion is softened. Add all other ingredients, except potatoes. Cook 30 to 45 minutes and then add potatoes. Cook this down to be as thick as desired. Add any seasoning you desire.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Top with 2/3 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Best served next day.

title: snow cream
directions: Mix egg, canned milk and vanilla.
Add to snow and add enough milk to make a thick slush.
Add enough sugar to suit your taste.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Make pudding first.
Stir together pudding and milk; set aside and cool.

title: vinaigrette dressing for spinach salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: ripe tomato pickles
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Put in stone jar and cover. This uncooked mixture must stand a week before using, but may be kept a year.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Take Cool Whip out of freezer; set aside.
Put candy bars in freezer.
Prepare brownies as directed in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. When done, cool 5 minutes, then take a fork and poke holes all through it.
Take coffee and sprinkle over brownies. Finish cooling. Cut in squares and divide in half.
Prepare chocolate mousse as directed.
Put in freezer for 1 hour or longer as needed. Remove candy. Keep divided and sliver with a sharp knife. Layer in bowl half the brownies, mousse, Cool Whip and candy; repeat.
Refrigerate 24 to 48 hours before serving.

title: sweet 'n sour cabbage casserole
directions: Saute turkey in skillet until no longer pink.
Add onion and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in seasonings.
Spread 3 cups cabbage in 2-quart baking dish.
Cover meat mixture and top with remaining 3 cups cabbage. Add brown sugar and vinegar to undiluted tomato soup.
Pour over top, cover and bake in 350°
oven about 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Mix all 5 ingredients well.
Put in refrigerator to thicken. When ready to cook, make into patties.
Roll in additional crumbs and fry in small amount of oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: ultimate chocolate brownies
directions: In a large bowl, combine cocoa and baking soda; blend in 1/3 cup melted margarine.
Add boiling water; stir until well blended. Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining margarine.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chunks.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Let cool.

title: jello jigglers
directions: Mix jello and Knox gelatine; add the boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add a little more water; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Can be cut into squares or use cookie cutters for shapes.

title: lasagne
directions: Boil noodles according to package directions.
Brown beef in skillet, drain fat.
Add seasoning, dry mix and cans of Italian sauce.
Mix well.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 15 minutes.

title: microwave walnut penuche
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil, letting foil extend above two sides.
Grease lightly (I spray with oil).
Spread nuts in a 9-inch microwave-safe pie plate.
Microwave on High
(uncovered) for 6 to 7 minutes, stirring 3 times, until lightly toasted.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Mash bananas in bowl.
Pour 1/2 cup strong prepared coffee and vanilla over them and let them stand while batter is being prepared.
Add melted margarine to brown sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs to the slightly cooled mixture.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
(The batter should be very stiff at this point.)
Add bananas and mix everything together.
Pour batter into 4 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 400° until toothpick comes out clean.
(Usually 1 hour for well done bread.)

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix and cream to consistency of butter. Roll into balls and flatten with a fork. Bake 12 minutes in 400° oven.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in wine, garlic powder and dressing for 1 hour.
Spread chicken in casserole and squeeze fresh lemon juice on top.
Spoon marinade over each piece.
Sprinkle with pepper and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: party fruit punch
directions: Mix together juices, water and sugar.
Pour into punch bowl. Add ginger ale and sherbet.
Serves 40 (6-ounce) glasses.

title: caldo con queso soup
directions: Combine water, tomato, onion, chiles, garlic and salt in a soup pan.
Bring to a boil and cook until vegetables are done. Blend in milk and soups.
Heat well.
Divide cheese into bowls and add hot soup and serve at once.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw dough and spread out on 12 x 15-inch bread pan (grease hands).
Beat egg and oregano together and brush half of it on dough.
In center section of dough, put a layer of pepperoni, then layer of Provolone cheese, layer of ham and a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Fold sides of dough over this and fasten with toothpicks. Brush remainder of egg mixture over outside of dough.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown.
Slice into 1-inch pieces.
May dip pieces in pizza sauce if desired.
Great finger food.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and cream cheese.
Stir in Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust or regular crust.
Double recipe for large crust.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and green pepper in butter.
Dilute soup with milk and add to vegetable mixture.
Combine all ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together soft oleo, regular oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Beat together with mixer.
Mix together and then add and beat well unsifted flour, baking powder, soda, cocoa, cloves and cinnamon.
Stir in zucchini.
Spoon mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with chocolate chips. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken spareribs
directions: Heat oil in nonstick skillet over a medium-high heat. Add chicken and lightly brown on all sides, turning frequently for about 6 to 7 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch dish.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Drain pineapple, saving 1/4 cup of syrup.
Lay pineapple, then yams in baking dish.
Pour syrup on top.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Cut in margarine. Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and place under broiler until browned.

title: barbecued beef patties
directions: Moisten crumbs with milk.
Combine with beef, salt and pepper. Shape into patties.
Put in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over patties and bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: baked beans routine
directions: Simmer onion, Linketts and yeast powder together.
Combine with beans, catsup, barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth and chill. Serve with assorted fresh fruit.

title: ham and cheese omelets
directions: Put stove on low heat.
In a bowl, mix eggs and water with a fork, briskly.
Place butter in frypan.
Pour egg mixture in the pan.
Let sit for 1 to 2 minutes, or until egg starts to bubble. Place the ham and cheese on top 1/2 of the egg. Wait until cheese starts to melt.
Fold egg over 1 time sideward and then forward. Enjoy.

title: jenel dessert
directions: Prepare the orange, cherry and lime flavors of gelatin separately using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each.
Pour each flavor into an 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm or overnight, then combine the lemon gelatin, sugar and remaining 1 cup boiling water; stir until gelatin and sugar are dissolved.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Meanwhile, mix the crumbs and melted butter; press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Cut the firm Jell-O into 1/2-inch cubes, then prepare whipped topping or use whipped cream from freezer.
Blend with lemon gelatin; fold in gelatin cubes. Pour into pan.
Chill at least 5 hours or overnight.
Run knife or spatula between side of pan before serving.
Additional topping may be spread on top if desired.

title: apple muffins
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder, nutmeg and 1 cup sugar. Cut in shortening.
Add eggs, milk and apples.
Mix just to moisten.
Spoon into greased muffin tins to 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from tins while hot.
When cool enough to handle, dip top of muffins into melted oleo, then in mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Mix together the hamburger, beans and taco seasoning.
Mix together lettuce, tomato and onions. Garnish with sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with any type tortilla chips, Fritos, etc.

title: corn & bacon soup
directions: Fry bacon, do not pour out grease. Add onion to grease and cook while you tear bacon in pieces and then add it back to the grease. Add corn and milk and cook until hot. Add hot sauce if desired. Serve with oyster crackers.

title: chicken souffle(serves 8)
directions: Put bread cubes in 9 x 9-inch square dish.
Mix together meat, vegetables and salad dressing.
Spread evenly over bread cubes. Top with bread slices.
Spread soup over top.
Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Then pour slowly over all.
Let stand in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° (325° in Pyrex) for 1 1/2 hours. Sprinkle cheese over top last 5 minutes of baking.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Beat together the molasses, egg and Crisco until thick.
Add sugar, milk, soda, flour, salt and spices.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Roll out next morning, not too thin.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Can be made in the morning and baked in the afternoon.

title: fudgy chocolate cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa; cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture will be dry). Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in medium saucepan over medium heat, melt 1 cup chips with sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Pour evenly over prepared crust.
Top with nuts and remaining 1 cup chips; press down firmly.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Chill if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store tightly covered.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Lightly brown the onion and green peppers in bacon drippings. Combine all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 375° until bubbly and browned on top.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Layer tortillas.
Cover with mixture of remaining ingredients. Repeat.
Makes large casserole.

title: hamdingers
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 tablespoon syrup.
Thread ham and pineapple alternately on skewers.
Combine syrup, sugar, honey and mustard.
Cook ham over low coals 15 to 20 minutes, brushing frequently with glaze.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and oleo well.
Add flour and buttermilk, a little at a time to sugar mixture, then add rest of dry ingredients.
Add one egg at a time to mixture and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into four 9-inch pans and bake at 350° in preheated oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well; store in large container and refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Combine jelly and mustard, heat until melted.
Slice hot dogs into 6 pieces and add to mixture.
Cook until hot dogs are done.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix is ready.
Take 3 or 4 tablespoons of mix and put into cup; just add hot water. Marshmallows can be added (optional).

title: unbaked marshmallow squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Cook eggs, sugar and butter over low heat until thick.
Cool; add vanilla.
Pour over crumb mixture and mix well.
Press into greased shallow pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours or more.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Tear crisp lettuce into bite size pieces.
Layer rest of ingredients in order given.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread over the top as you would frosting.
Top with grated cheese.

title: creamy chicken pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta according to directions; add broccoli, carrot, onions and green pepper the last 5 minutes (don't overcook). Drain.
Add water to liquid from chicken to make 3/4 cup and combine in ingredients.
Add soup and cheese.
Heat to boiling. Add the pasta mixture to chicken and heat through, stirring frequently.
Serves 5.

title: hidden valley ranch quesadillas
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Spread over 5 tortillas.
Place top.
Brush tops with oil.
Broil until golden brown.
Turn.
Broil until cheese is melted.
Cut into 8 wedges.

title: l.j.'s pilaf
directions: Cook onion soup in 2 cups of water for 10 minutes; set aside. Melt butter in a large skillet.
Break up vermicelli and measure 2 cups.
Brown vermicelli pieces in melted butter by stirring constantly over medium heat.
Add 1 cup of Minute rice, consomme and onion soup.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until all liquid is absorbed.
May be made ahead and reheated in microwave.
Goes well with grilled meat!

title: holloway's thursday night regular "mandatory meat loaf with flavor"
directions: Mix all ingredients into a glass Corning Ware dish.
Spray with Pam.
(For better results, mix up the night before and let stand in refrigerator until next evening.)
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes, then drain all grease and if desired use drippings for gravy.
Bake uncovered.
Not a low-fat recipe.
Enough for 6 hearty mouths and then some.

title: pizza dip
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Thin with milk so that it is like a paste.
Put on a pizza plate or a large plate.
Put the shrimp sauce over the cream cheese.
Place the shrimp, onions and cheese on the sauce. Refrigerate.
Can be made a day before serving. Take out of refrigerator awhile before serving.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: reindeer sandwich
directions: Cut off crust from bread.
Cut bread in half.
Form 2 triangle shapes.
Spread peanut butter on one of your triangles.
Place other triangle on top of the one with peanut butter.
Stick on with honey the pretzels for ears, marshmallows with raisins on top for eyes and a cherry for his nose.

title: roma party mix
directions: In 2-gallon storage bag combine Crispix cereal, crackers and pretzel sticks.
Set aside.
Combine oil, hot pepper sauce, Italian seasoning and fennel seed.
Pour oil and spices over cereal mixture.
Close bag and gently toss cereal mixture until well coated.
Sprinkle cheese over cereal.
Close bag and gently toss cereal mixture until well coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Heat vegetable oil in frying pan. Dredge chops in flour and brown in vegetable oil.
Drain chops and place them in baking dish large enough for all chops to be flat on bottom of dish.
Combine vinegar, catsup, pineapple, sugar and salt.
Pour this mixture over pork chops.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally.
A little water can be added if sauce cooks down too soon.

title: fast fixin fruit and cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into 9 x 13-inch pan and tilt pan to cover bottom.
Put cake mix, eggs and water in pan.
Stir with fork until blended.
Spoon pie filling into batter and use fork to marble.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer in order listed and toss before serving.
Prepare and refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.

title: sausage and potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Cut sausage into slices (patties into quarters). Stir together all ingredients in large bowl. Pour mixture into baking dish. Bake 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place Tater Tots in bottom of dish. Fry steaks or Skallops and cut into bite size pieces. Layer on top of Tater Tots.
Next, add onions and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with cheese. Dilute soup with milk.
Add sour cream to this.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes (until Tater Tots are tender).

title: chocolate buttons
directions: In large bowl, combine margarine, sugar, chocolate and vanilla;
blend well.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill dough 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are set.
Remove from oven; press chocolate wafer in center of cookie.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet.

title: jeannine's swedish coffeecake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients as for pie crust.
Pat into 2 strips, 3-inches wide, on a cookie sheet.
Combine 1 cup water and 1/2 cup butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add flour all at once.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat in vanilla.
Spread on top of the 2 strips of pie crust.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost with powdered sugar glaze.

title: gwen's chocolate cake
directions: Cook slowly 1 cup milk, chocolate
and butter until it forms a custard.
Cool.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside. Beat eggs; add sugar gradually.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture alternately with 1 cup milk.
Add chocolate mix and 1 teaspoon vanilla to egg batter.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cracker jack popcorn
directions: Fill large roaster pan with 2 bags of microwave popcorn already popped.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Bring above ingredients to full boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over popped corn and mix well. Then bake in oven at 250° for 1 hour.

title: hailimaile chicken salad
directions: Eyeball the measurements.
Mix together.
It's a winner! A hui hou!

title: pork chop delight
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides; drain off fat.
Cover with water.
Put in the bouillon cubes and let it simmer down, uncovered.
Very, very good.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Pour over vegetables.
Makes 1/2 gallon.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Keeps in refrigerator for weeks.
Real good.

title: hush puppies(makes a large quantity.)
directions: Mix together.
Add just enough water to make a thick mixture. Make into balls.

title: caramel german chocolate bars
directions: In top of double boiler, combine caramels and 1/3 cup milk. Cook over hot water, stirring until melted (set aside).

title: strawberry satin pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Cool.
Put on a layer of sliced almonds (toasted).
Combine and mix the 1/2 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons cornstarch, flour and salt and cook until thick.
Cool, then chill. Fold in whipped cream and vanilla.
Pour in shell and slice berries over this.
Cover with glaze made of 1/2 cup strawberries and 1/2 cup water.
Cook 2 minutes (sieve).
Mix the 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Gradually add to juice and cook until thick and clear.
Cool and spoon over top.
Chill.

title: quickie cobbler
directions: Melt putter in baking dish Mix milk, flour and sugar; pour over butter; add fruit. Bake at 350° for 30 - 40 minutes.

title: hibachi grilled zucchini
directions: Place in plastic bag olive oil, basil and garlic powder.
Peel and slice zucchini lengthwise in thick pieces.
Place zucchini in bag with other ingredients and shake.
Cook zucchini on grill until nicely browned.

title: fresh fruit ambrosia
directions: Combine the orange juice, 7-Up and banana in a blender; puree until smooth.
Pour over fresh fruit mixture.
Sprinkle with the nutmeg and cardamon.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Sprinkle on the coconut and serve immediately.
This has no cholesterol, no fat and no sodium; is a good source of potassium.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, melted butter or margarine (that has cooled), salt and 2 cups flour. Stir until well blended, then add remaining flour (1 1/2 to 1 3/4 cups).
Dough should not be sticky.

title: bulgur-rice pilaf(low-fat)
directions: Note: Precooked cracked wheat (bulgur) adds a nutty flavor to this dish.

title: italian beef
directions: Place beef in large Dutch oven half filled with water.
Add salt and sliced onion, roasting until tender.
Remove from oven and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Remove roast and liquid to large glass or steel container.
Next day remove fat and slice very, very thin.

title: cabbage patch stew(makes 8 servings)
directions: Saute meat, bell pepper, onion and celery until brown. Add other ingredients. Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Simmer until cabbage is done.

title: hominy grits spoon bread
directions: Cook milk and grits until thick, stirring constantly.
Add butter, sugar and salt.
Let mixture cool, then add egg yolks beaten and baking powder.
Beat egg whites stiff, fold in mixture. Put in greased casserole, set pan in warm water.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: lasagne florentine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, egg, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and spinach.
Mix to blend well.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a bowl; set aside.
Add all other ingredients in another bowl.
Slowly add dry ingredients to this bowl until completely mixed.
Use teaspoon to scoop batter up and make into a ball.
Place on a cookie sheet and flatten with a fork in two directions.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together with beater:
peanut butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla.
Place in pie shell and chill for several hours.
Just before serving, top with chopped peanuts.

title: chocolate filled angel food cake
directions: Combine the cocoa, sugar, salt and cream.
Chill for 1 hour. Whip the chilled mixture.
Cut a 1-inch layer from the top of the angel food cake.
Cut out the middle of the cake, leaving walls and bottom about 1-inch thick.
Fill the cavity with 1/3 of the cream mixture and 1/3 of the almonds.
Replace the top of the cake.
Frost with the remaining cake mixture and sprinkle the remaining almonds over the top and sides.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: jalapeno squares
directions: Beat eggs well and fold in cheese.
Generously grease a 9-inch pan.
Place peppers (sliced) in bottom and pour egg mixture on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken in pockets(makes 8 servings)
directions: On each of eight squares of aluminum foil, place one piece of cleaned, raw chicken and 1/8 of the other ingredients.
Place in uncovered roaster and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: no-cook fruitcake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add marshmallows, milk, graham cracker crumbs, nuts, coconut (optional) and candied fruit which has been cut in pieces.
Use a large pan and mix with hands.
Use graham cracker box to store cake.
Press in box lined with buttered wax paper.
Store in refrigerator.

title: texas beer bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add can of beer and stir just until well blended.
Transfer into bread pan.
Let rise for 10 minutes.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tomali pie
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and hamburger.
Add and then simmer tomato sauce, corn, olives, sugar, salt, pepper and chili powder and cheese.
Place in baking dish and top with corn bread, eggs, milk and shortening.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tomato relish
directions: Combine all in a large kettle.
Bring this to a hard boil and boil for 15 minutes.
Place in jars and seal.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Take bread and cut each slice into 5 strips.
Roll strips like a cinnamon roll and place on top of peaches.

title: creamy lemon cheesecake pie(makes 6 servings)
directions: Beat cream cheese in bowl of electric mixer fitted with paddle attachment on medium speed until creamy. Add sugar; beat until well blended.

Add sour cream, lemon juice and peel; mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing on low speed after each addition just until blended. Pour batter into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool completely on wire rack. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
